1
00:01:27,775 --> 00:01:29,388
Is Mrs Laxmi Chaudhary in?
- Yes.

2
00:01:29,607 --> 00:01:31,946
Sister, someone has
come to meet you.

3
00:01:32,487 --> 00:01:36,098
Do come in and sit down.
- Our duty is to keep standing, Madam.

4
00:01:39,039 --> 00:01:42,593
Yes? What is it?
- We're from the Income Tax.

5
00:01:42,673 --> 00:01:45,558
Your husband has been raided.
Let's go immediately.

6
00:01:45,743 --> 00:01:48,293
My God! What do I do now?
- Don't worry, sister.

7
00:01:48,373 --> 00:01:51,098
They're only Income Tax officers,
they won't harm you.

8
00:01:51,284 --> 00:01:52,761
I'll accompany you.
Let's go.

9
00:02:08,774 --> 00:02:10,894
Where's your master?
- He's inside.

10
00:02:22,701 --> 00:02:26,538
We are doomed, Saraswati!
We are ruined!

11
00:02:26,618 --> 00:02:29,226
What do I do now?

12
00:02:35,654 --> 00:02:36,795
How often...

13
00:02:38,475 --> 00:02:43,605
have I asked you not to hide the keys
of the locker behind God's picture?!

14
00:02:44,390 --> 00:02:47,993
We've been raided now, haven't we?!
They'll take all away now!

15
00:02:48,437 --> 00:02:50,831
The gold, the cash...
and this house!

16
00:02:50,911 --> 00:02:53,435
No! Not the house!

17
00:02:53,515 --> 00:02:56,329
They'll take away
everything. Everything!

18
00:02:56,734 --> 00:03:01,969
No! Please save this house!
I beg of you!

19
00:03:02,049 --> 00:03:04,357
Please don't render
us homeless.

20
00:03:04,437 --> 00:03:08,942
Very well. Since today is our
25th wedding anniversary...

21
00:03:09,526 --> 00:03:11,171
I can't refuse you anything.

22
00:03:12,632 --> 00:03:15,040
I will do then, that which...

23
00:03:16,616 --> 00:03:19,269
every sensible husband does!

24
00:03:22,882 --> 00:03:26,177
Here's the 100 Rupees...
Get going.

25
00:03:26,257 --> 00:03:27,889
Only a hundred rupees, sir?

26
00:03:27,969 --> 00:03:32,348
Now look; I was born after
the death of a 1000 misers!

27
00:03:32,901 --> 00:03:34,883
Quietly take this...
or you get nothing!

28
00:03:35,269 --> 00:03:37,548
I'll even call the cops
and tell them that...

29
00:03:37,891 --> 00:03:42,026
some guys from the films posed
as policemen and kidnapped my wife!

30
00:03:42,264 --> 00:03:44,412
We've done just as you
asked us to, sir.

31
00:03:44,813 --> 00:03:46,720
But we get more money
to speak our lines!

32
00:03:47,393 --> 00:03:49,227
You ought to be
large-hearted today...

33
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:51,255
let's the silver jubilee
of your wedding, after all!

34
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:57,309
Here's 10 more rupees...
and just get lost!

35
00:03:57,389 --> 00:03:58,429
Thank you.

36
00:04:00,477 --> 00:04:03,055
Weren't they from the Income Tax, 
brother-in-law?

37
00:04:03,135 --> 00:04:05,791
You were conned, weren't you?

38
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:08,182
Where was the need
to do all that?

39
00:04:09,545 --> 00:04:12,783
When a wife goes away to
her parents' place on...

40
00:04:12,976 --> 00:04:17,494
her 25th wedding anniversary,
what does a man do?

41
00:04:17,574 --> 00:04:21,546
Your practical jokes will
ruin this home someday!

42
00:04:22,776 --> 00:04:25,961
There's a limit! What if I had
suffered a heart-attack?

43
00:04:26,041 --> 00:04:28,664
A heart-attack? Do you
have the heart, then?

44
00:04:28,969 --> 00:04:33,518
Hadn't you given it away to me
25 years ago on our nuptial night?

45
00:04:33,598 --> 00:04:36,131
Hush! Can't you see your
sister-in-law here?!

46
00:04:36,211 --> 00:04:38,488
You're scaring me as if
she were a gun!

47
00:04:38,568 --> 00:04:40,994
She's only a sister-in-law...
a half-wife!

48
00:04:41,462 --> 00:04:42,716
Now wait...

49
00:04:49,599 --> 00:04:53,910
Here you are!
- Wow! It's beautiful!

50
00:04:54,107 --> 00:04:55,810
Is this for me?
- Of course!

51
00:04:55,890 --> 00:05:01,110
Looks like you will always
play jokes and buy gold!

52
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:03,046
I might get over the
habit of playing jokes.

53
00:05:03,843 --> 00:05:06,996
But to admire the beauty of
the girls from the villages...

54
00:05:08,006 --> 00:05:10,433
who are no less than
real gold...

55
00:05:11,158 --> 00:05:12,993
I will never get over
my admiration for them.

56
00:05:19,663 --> 00:05:23,855
Congratulations on your
wedding anniversary!

57
00:05:25,026 --> 00:05:28,660
See how much your son loves
you both, brother-in-law?

58
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:30,516
He's bound you both
in just one garland!

59
00:05:30,596 --> 00:05:33,599
It's Amit who will be bound
in matrimony now.

60
00:05:33,797 --> 00:05:37,738
That's the gift I give you
on my anniversary, my son!

61
00:05:37,818 --> 00:05:40,329
There you go again!
Now yet, daddy!

62
00:05:40,409 --> 00:05:42,610
You know marriage is going
to cost me dearly.

63
00:05:42,690 --> 00:05:44,263
I've got to go to London for
my business-management course!

64
00:05:44,343 --> 00:05:46,462
I've got to begin my career!
You know that, don't you?

65
00:05:46,625 --> 00:05:50,639
There's no career bigger than
finding a good wife!

66
00:05:50,812 --> 00:05:52,049
Look at your Mom...

67
00:05:52,129 --> 00:05:55,353
I've had it made, ever since
I got married to her!

68
00:05:55,951 --> 00:06:00,923
And she even gave me
a certificate in you!

69
00:06:01,599 --> 00:06:05,142
I've even found a girl.

70
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:09,097
I've only got to visit
Nirmal Village to finalise it.

71
00:06:09,177 --> 00:06:10,723
A village?

72
00:06:11,470 --> 00:06:17,167
You speak as if the word
has set your town on fire!

73
00:06:17,494 --> 00:06:19,845
Yes, it's a village!
The Nirmal Village!

74
00:06:20,598 --> 00:06:23,311
There's a beautiful girl there...

75
00:06:23,391 --> 00:06:24,977
who will be my daughter-in-law!

76
00:06:25,339 --> 00:06:27,776
I even have a picture.
Want to see it?

77
00:06:27,856 --> 00:06:30,653
No thank you!
Because it won't help!

78
00:06:31,524 --> 00:06:34,715
We have a sensible son, Laxmi!

79
00:06:35,156 --> 00:06:39,290
He knows, no one can change
his father's decision!

80
00:06:39,373 --> 00:06:42,288
Now look, Dad...
don't talk about that!

81
00:06:42,653 --> 00:06:45,741
I know how you got used
to liking bitter-gourd!

82
00:06:46,170 --> 00:06:50,179
Don't you know? Bitter-gourd
is fantastic for health!

83
00:06:50,463 --> 00:06:52,251
It cleanses the system!

84
00:06:52,539 --> 00:06:54,482
It's good for the heart
and the brain, you know?

85
00:06:54,562 --> 00:06:56,345
I don't ! You're lying!

86
00:06:56,506 --> 00:06:58,678
There's only one thing that's
good for the heart!

87
00:06:58,908 --> 00:07:00,634
You must have a heart,
that is!

88
00:07:07,828 --> 00:07:10,449
Tomorrow's the Independence
Day of the India.

89
00:07:10,970 --> 00:07:12,887
I've been invited over
by the Headmaster...

90
00:07:12,967 --> 00:07:14,972
and the girl belongs to
the same village!

91
00:07:16,337 --> 00:07:18,184
That's called killing two
birds with one stone!

92
00:07:56,466 --> 00:07:57,875
Raise your voice, children!

93
00:07:57,955 --> 00:08:00,375
Glory to Mother India!

94
00:08:00,455 --> 00:08:02,390
Glory to Mother India!

95
00:08:04,644 --> 00:08:09,671
I will request our Chief
Guest, Mr Chaudhary,...

96
00:08:09,894 --> 00:08:12,176
to say a few words
to the children.

97
00:08:15,665 --> 00:08:20,891
Dear children, you are the
citizens of tomorrow.

98
00:08:22,563 --> 00:08:25,172
I will say more than
a few words.

99
00:08:27,518 --> 00:08:29,737
It has to do with the
slogan you chanted...

100
00:08:30,288 --> 00:08:32,007
Glory to Mother India

101
00:08:33,147 --> 00:08:36,121
I want to know what Glory
to Mother India means.

102
00:08:36,201 --> 00:08:39,142
I want to know the importance
of the word Mother India

103
00:08:39,367 --> 00:08:42,422
I will reward anyone who
gives me the right answer.

104
00:09:01,110 --> 00:09:02,602
I'm surprised, children!

105
00:09:03,008 --> 00:09:05,608
Don't you know the meaning
of the expression...

106
00:09:05,929 --> 00:09:07,465
you were just chanting?

107
00:09:10,521 --> 00:09:12,108
Is there no one in
the village...

108
00:09:12,305 --> 00:09:14,253
who knows what the expression
Mother India means?

109
00:09:18,475 --> 00:09:22,706
Go on... of course!

110
00:09:23,423 --> 00:09:24,718
I can give you the answer!

111
00:09:25,082 --> 00:09:27,063
Wonderful!
Do come forward, Madhuri!

112
00:09:27,416 --> 00:09:31,021
She's the one I told
you about, Mr Chaudhary.

113
00:09:31,101 --> 00:09:32,101
I recognised her.

114
00:09:32,837 --> 00:09:34,607
Greetings.

115
00:09:34,794 --> 00:09:37,723
Yes, dear? Should you
know the answer...

116
00:09:37,803 --> 00:09:40,624
you might get the reward.

117
00:09:44,921 --> 00:09:47,816
By Mother India, we are
referring to our nation.

118
00:09:48,203 --> 00:09:49,918
From Kashmir to Kanyakumari...

119
00:09:50,156 --> 00:09:52,140
from the Arabian Seas
to the Bay of Bengal...

120
00:09:52,540 --> 00:09:54,124
all the religions and
faiths that it fosters...

121
00:09:54,204 --> 00:09:58,720
the Bible, the Geeta and the Koran
symbolise the spirit of India.

122
00:09:59,076 --> 00:10:01,240
Mother India is the soul
of the nation...

123
00:10:01,531 --> 00:10:06,081
that is worshipped
even by the Gods.

124
00:10:06,281 --> 00:10:08,234
Which is why it is
called Mother India.

125
00:10:09,483 --> 00:10:12,157
Let's say together then.
To India...

126
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:15,632
Glory be!

127
00:10:17,770 --> 00:10:19,133
Mother!

128
00:10:20,303 --> 00:10:22,802
Where are you, mother?!

129
00:10:23,576 --> 00:10:26,981
Madhuri has won a reward!

130
00:10:27,065 --> 00:10:29,679
And the gentleman is personally
coming here to give her the reward!

131
00:10:29,759 --> 00:10:33,079
Let's go out and see!
They must've arrived in their car.

132
00:10:41,498 --> 00:10:43,162
Mother!
- Come dear.

133
00:10:46,161 --> 00:10:47,290
Welcome...

134
00:10:47,876 --> 00:10:52,733
This is Mr Chaudhary I spoke
to you about, Ganga.

135
00:10:53,894 --> 00:10:58,229
You should've told us about
your visit. I'd have...

136
00:10:58,309 --> 00:11:00,632
Please don't worry.

137
00:11:01,153 --> 00:11:04,443
The Head Master invited
us to the school today.

138
00:11:04,713 --> 00:11:07,371
And we thought we could deal
with both things today.

139
00:11:07,736 --> 00:11:10,401
Deal with what?
- I'll explain.

140
00:11:10,861 --> 00:11:15,822
I am greatly influenced
by my wife, Laxmi...

141
00:11:15,902 --> 00:11:18,513
because she comes from the villages.
I believe that...

142
00:11:18,593 --> 00:11:22,815
the beauty of the villages has a purity
and nobility that is lacking in cities

143
00:11:23,123 --> 00:11:25,947
We have a son for whom
we had ideas...

144
00:11:26,132 --> 00:11:29,510
after we saw a photograph
of Madhuri.

145
00:11:29,695 --> 00:11:33,495
Now that we have met her and
seen how intelligent she is...

146
00:11:33,575 --> 00:11:36,143
we have a greater idea!
Am I right?

147
00:11:36,398 --> 00:11:40,110
It's time now to give
you the award, my dear.

148
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:45,368
We want to give our son to you
for life, as your reward.

149
00:11:47,810 --> 00:11:51,716
We consider the alliance
sealed, if you don't mind.

150
00:11:54,966 --> 00:11:59,512
Mr Chaudhary! I can't
begin to express myself!

151
00:12:00,341 --> 00:12:03,752
To think that my daughter will be the
daughter-in-law of a rich household...

152
00:12:04,522 --> 00:12:06,761
is something I couldn't
even dream about!

153
00:12:07,081 --> 00:12:10,401
Madhuri must've done something
good to deserve this.

154
00:12:10,481 --> 00:12:12,801
Let's discuss the dowry first.

155
00:12:12,881 --> 00:12:15,441
Mr Chaudhary! 
Are you talking of dowry?!

156
00:12:15,521 --> 00:12:17,736
Of course, I want a dowry!

157
00:12:18,676 --> 00:12:21,802
Because dowry is now
part of our culture!

158
00:12:22,931 --> 00:12:26,573
Even after 25 years in the city,
I have not forgotten our culture.

159
00:12:27,607 --> 00:12:29,486
As part of the dowry...

160
00:12:30,953 --> 00:12:33,928
I want some bitter-gourd,
some green-grams...

161
00:12:34,266 --> 00:12:37,193
snake-gourd, a pickle
of green-chillies...

162
00:12:37,273 --> 00:12:39,146
and before I end
my meal...

163
00:12:39,226 --> 00:12:42,268
I want a porridge garnished
with dates and dry-fruits!

164
00:12:44,661 --> 00:12:50,706
As dowry, I need a meal
that Madhuri has cooked.

165
00:12:51,388 --> 00:12:54,665
Fantastic! Your daughter is
good looking and talented!

166
00:12:55,035 --> 00:12:56,567
This food that she
has cooked...

167
00:12:56,647 --> 00:12:58,772
will leave me licking my
fingers for years to come!

168
00:12:59,012 --> 00:13:02,092
Won't you have a
wedding date fixed, then?

169
00:13:02,389 --> 00:13:03,821
I'm not a fool!

170
00:13:04,292 --> 00:13:07,972
I even had the wedding date
fixed, before we came here.

171
00:13:08,796 --> 00:13:11,812
Tuesday next is considered
to be very auspicious.

172
00:13:12,338 --> 00:13:14,457
You have no objections, do you?

173
00:13:14,537 --> 00:13:17,886
How can we ?
We are fortunate indeed!

174
00:13:18,744 --> 00:13:22,413
Can I've the good-fortune of meeting
my sister's future husband?

175
00:13:22,493 --> 00:13:24,990
My sister answered your
questions and won a reward.

176
00:13:25,141 --> 00:13:27,133
I will question your son, too...

177
00:13:27,213 --> 00:13:31,880
and should he win, 
I will give him my sister in marriage!

178
00:13:32,387 --> 00:13:34,892
Certainly! Why not?
Let's go together.

179
00:13:35,812 --> 00:13:38,746
I'm grateful to you, Teacher.

180
00:13:39,433 --> 00:13:42,113
It's thanks to you that my
son's fortunes have looked up.

181
00:14:02,168 --> 00:14:04,201
Your future brother-in-law
is here to meet you!

182
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,770
What do you mean?
- Yes.

183
00:14:07,386 --> 00:14:10,004
I've met the girl and
even fixed your wedding.

184
00:14:11,036 --> 00:14:13,641
Have you even decided who
my brother-in-law will be?

185
00:14:13,887 --> 00:14:16,248
I've never let anything
be half-done.

186
00:14:16,685 --> 00:14:17,856
Now look...

187
00:14:18,207 --> 00:14:21,304
your brother-in-law wants
to interview you.

188
00:14:21,384 --> 00:14:22,934
An interview?!
- Yes.

189
00:14:23,336 --> 00:14:26,661
He's a simpleton
from the countryside.

190
00:14:26,959 --> 00:14:29,522
You must deliberately lose...
which will make him happy.

191
00:14:29,602 --> 00:14:31,174
But I've already
lost out, father.

192
00:14:33,258 --> 00:14:35,723
Shreekant!
- Coming over...!

193
00:14:45,424 --> 00:14:46,739
Brother-in-law!

194
00:14:47,641 --> 00:14:48,964
What misbehaviour is this?!

195
00:14:49,404 --> 00:14:52,841
Not misbehaviour. That is the
tradition of our family!

196
00:14:52,921 --> 00:14:56,095
You look like a film-star!

197
00:14:56,736 --> 00:14:58,651
My sister is indeed
very fortunate!

198
00:14:59,038 --> 00:15:00,924
He's my son, after all.

199
00:15:01,123 --> 00:15:03,455
But hurry up and ask him
whatever you wish to.

200
00:15:05,478 --> 00:15:07,558
My first question is...

201
00:15:07,924 --> 00:15:10,970
what would happen, had we
not had the Himalayas?

202
00:15:11,232 --> 00:15:13,363
That's an extremely
stupid question!

203
00:15:13,739 --> 00:15:17,478
It's a great question!
Answer him, Amit!

204
00:15:18,182 --> 00:15:21,175
Even the kids know that if
it wasn't for the Himalayas...

205
00:15:21,255 --> 00:15:23,299
foreign powers would have
attacked our country.

206
00:15:23,864 --> 00:15:27,710
Wonderful!
You're incomparable!

207
00:15:28,623 --> 00:15:29,749
My second question is...

208
00:15:29,829 --> 00:15:36,138
what would we have, if
not the Himalayas?

209
00:15:37,132 --> 00:15:38,874
What?!
- Of course! Answer me.

210
00:15:38,954 --> 00:15:42,021
What would we have,
if not the Himalayas? - What?

211
00:15:42,101 --> 00:15:44,758
What would we have,
if not the Swiss Alps?

212
00:15:46,684 --> 00:15:48,312
Had it not been
for the alps...

213
00:15:48,514 --> 00:15:50,592
the cool winds would've ruined
the crops in our nation.

214
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:52,219
Just as I am being ruined!

215
00:15:55,018 --> 00:15:57,033
You're an intelligent man!

216
00:15:57,113 --> 00:15:59,443
You score 101 marks
out of 100!

217
00:16:00,305 --> 00:16:03,921
My third is question is
a bit tricky. Be careful.

218
00:16:04,695 --> 00:16:06,833
What would happen, if we
had not the Swiss Alps?

219
00:16:07,792 --> 00:16:12,710
You've trapped him!
Do you have an answer?

220
00:16:17,981 --> 00:16:19,798
I give up to you and to...

221
00:16:19,878 --> 00:16:22,285
this chap you've chosen
for my brother-in-law!

222
00:16:22,365 --> 00:16:25,316
I don't know the answer!
- I'll explain!

223
00:16:25,583 --> 00:16:28,941
What would Tensingh climb,
if not the Swiss Alps?

224
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:32,701
Bravo! That's wonderful!

225
00:16:33,624 --> 00:16:38,895
What's up? Why are you
winking at me?

226
00:16:39,466 --> 00:16:42,943
What's the mystery all about?
- It's a bad omen actually.

227
00:16:43,327 --> 00:16:46,190
A blinking eye is considered
to be inauspicious.

228
00:16:46,270 --> 00:16:50,206
And I have both eyes shutting up!
- Must be conjunctivitis!

229
00:16:50,541 --> 00:16:54,021
It has spread in the whole city!
Let me put give you some eye-drops.

230
00:16:54,101 --> 00:16:56,221
No thank you! You need
the eye-drops actually!

231
00:16:56,570 --> 00:16:59,804
For what is going on in
the name of Swiss Alps...

232
00:16:59,884 --> 00:17:02,453
should you cure your eyes,
mine will be fine, too!

233
00:17:04,517 --> 00:17:08,039
I spoke of your sight...
and you talk of attitudes!

234
00:17:08,704 --> 00:17:10,748
Let's go and eat, Shrikant.

235
00:17:12,749 --> 00:17:16,918
Wow! I have yet to eat
something so delicious!

236
00:17:16,998 --> 00:17:20,853
Look! Don't we both
share the same tastes?

237
00:17:21,554 --> 00:17:23,536
Tell me something;
my sister will accompany...

238
00:17:23,616 --> 00:17:26,354
your son to London after
the wedding, won't she?

239
00:17:26,621 --> 00:17:28,125
But naturally!

240
00:17:28,618 --> 00:17:31,605
The couple will live
together after their wedding.

241
00:17:31,685 --> 00:17:34,190
Get the Rasagollas for
Shrikant. It's in the fridge.

242
00:17:34,270 --> 00:17:37,683
Maharaj...
- Go and fetch it yourself!

243
00:17:37,895 --> 00:17:39,485
Please go and fetch it!

244
00:17:39,565 --> 00:17:40,722
Okay.

245
00:17:45,322 --> 00:17:47,280
Now listen, son...
I have something to ask you.

246
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:48,347
Yes. Go on...

247
00:17:48,427 --> 00:17:51,533
I'm told that village folks
bury gold in their courtyard.

248
00:17:51,999 --> 00:17:55,373
It's true. I've heard of it, too.

249
00:17:56,293 --> 00:17:58,530
In the marriage of
your sister, then...

250
00:17:58,610 --> 00:18:01,365
Listen! Where are the rasagollas ?

251
00:18:01,589 --> 00:18:05,450
It's in my room. In my
briefcase, actually.

252
00:18:05,875 --> 00:18:08,494
In your briefcase?
- Yes. Hurry up and fetch it.

253
00:18:10,784 --> 00:18:13,943
Weren't you asking
me something, sir?

254
00:18:14,023 --> 00:18:16,545
I was telling you
something, actually.

255
00:18:17,022 --> 00:18:19,419
It's a marriage, after all.
It's no joke...

256
00:18:19,980 --> 00:18:23,522
so much of the buried gold does
your sister get in marriage?

257
00:18:24,896 --> 00:18:27,325
You will give her atleast
200 grams of gold, won't you?

258
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:36,306
200 grams? But of course!

259
00:18:36,386 --> 00:18:41,123
I must give her that much...
naturally!

260
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:43,440
In fact, you can consider
it given to her already!

261
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:44,708
I'll be back in a minute!

262
00:18:48,622 --> 00:18:52,759
Won't you have the rasagollas ?
- No thank you. I've had enough.

263
00:18:54,868 --> 00:18:57,769
Well... have you been
up to your jokes again?

264
00:18:57,849 --> 00:18:59,318
Not at all!

265
00:19:00,499 --> 00:19:02,471
I've set the stage for a joke though!

266
00:19:06,862 --> 00:19:08,350
What am I to do now?

267
00:19:08,709 --> 00:19:10,437
Although it's the question
of my sister's life...

268
00:19:10,517 --> 00:19:12,145
where will I bring
200 grams of gold from?

269
00:19:12,225 --> 00:19:15,149
I will have to face
this problem somehow!

270
00:19:15,229 --> 00:19:18,189
My sister will surely be
married! She surely will!

271
00:19:22,242 --> 00:19:25,033
If it wasn't for
our jokes...

272
00:19:25,453 --> 00:19:28,262
life would be so
dull and drab!

273
00:19:28,908 --> 00:19:35,224
Jokes and laughter add
years to one's life.

274
00:19:35,613 --> 00:19:37,986
Isn't that why both of us
are in the pink of health?

275
00:19:38,908 --> 00:19:40,157
Welcome, Shreekant.

276
00:19:45,044 --> 00:19:47,814
Do we have a deal, then?
- What is the deal?

277
00:19:48,413 --> 00:19:50,543
That one about the 200
grams of gold, of course!

278
00:19:50,623 --> 00:19:52,927
Naturally! It was a deal the
moment you mentioned it!

279
00:19:53,007 --> 00:19:57,360
Let's shake then...
Come on!

280
00:19:57,440 --> 00:20:02,066
Give this sari to Madhuri
and tell her...

281
00:20:02,412 --> 00:20:04,465
that it's a token of
our affection for her.

282
00:20:05,561 --> 00:20:09,511
We're now waiting for
the auspicious moment...

283
00:20:10,128 --> 00:20:14,243
when she comes here as
our daughter-in-law.

284
00:20:46,275 --> 00:20:48,016
"It's like adding
spice to life..."

285
00:20:48,096 --> 00:20:50,381
"when the groom is
fairer than the bride"

286
00:20:53,981 --> 00:20:58,200
"The one who steals the heart
is fairer than his bride..."

287
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:06,237
"How do you like them?
Fair-skinned or dark?"

288
00:21:10,721 --> 00:21:14,627
"Tell me how you'd like
your husband to be?"

289
00:21:14,707 --> 00:21:19,477
"Let me go...
don't pester me"

290
00:21:26,903 --> 00:21:30,708
"How do I tell you
or explain..."

291
00:21:30,788 --> 00:21:35,025
"my choice is hidden
deep down in my heart"

292
00:22:18,980 --> 00:22:23,056
"It'll be difficult to
woo the fair-skinned one..."

293
00:22:23,136 --> 00:22:26,877
"and the dark one will
attract taunts from everyone"

294
00:22:36,837 --> 00:22:40,842
"Be he fair-skinned
or dark..."

295
00:22:40,922 --> 00:22:44,636
"It is he.
I will have to live with"

296
00:22:44,716 --> 00:22:46,749
"The fair-skinned one
will be an arrogant one..."

297
00:22:46,829 --> 00:22:48,675
"while the dark one will
suffer from complexes"

298
00:22:48,755 --> 00:22:52,408
"You will lose your sleep
and be restless"

299
00:22:52,634 --> 00:22:56,606
"Do tell me then... what
kind of a husband d'you want?"

300
00:22:56,686 --> 00:23:01,742
"Let me go...
do not pester me"

301
00:23:02,472 --> 00:23:06,293
"How do I tell you
or explain this..."

302
00:23:06,373 --> 00:23:10,262
"My choice lies hidden
deep down in my heart"

303
00:23:50,027 --> 00:23:53,960
"Should he be tall
or short in height?"

304
00:23:54,040 --> 00:23:58,089
"Should he be skinny
or plump like a wrestler?"

305
00:24:07,771 --> 00:24:11,613
"Be he skinny or strong..."

306
00:24:11,693 --> 00:24:15,497
"I only hope he is not
evil at heart"

307
00:24:15,577 --> 00:24:17,545
"The tall one will
inflict cruelties..."

308
00:24:17,625 --> 00:24:19,446
"the shorter one will
look odd"

309
00:24:19,526 --> 00:24:21,433
"How will you take the weight..."

310
00:24:21,513 --> 00:24:23,379
"should you find a fat husband?"

311
00:24:23,459 --> 00:24:27,339
"Do tell us then... what kind
of a husband do you want?"

312
00:24:27,419 --> 00:24:31,990
"Do let me go... don't pester me"

313
00:24:33,281 --> 00:24:36,867
"How do I explain
or tell you..."

314
00:24:37,187 --> 00:24:41,109
"My choice lies in my dreams"

315
00:25:08,176 --> 00:25:12,245
"What is this I hear,
my friend..."

316
00:25:12,662 --> 00:25:16,360
"that they've chosen
a city-bred for you?"

317
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:20,369
"The city-bred have a
colourful nature..."

318
00:25:20,449 --> 00:25:24,258
"They're always chasing
the pretty ones"

319
00:25:24,338 --> 00:25:28,284
"I shall turn myself into
what he'd like..."

320
00:25:28,364 --> 00:25:32,023
"and win over my
husband's heart"

321
00:25:32,308 --> 00:25:36,230
"What if you slip
and fumble?"

322
00:25:36,310 --> 00:25:40,181
"Whom will you tell the
truth, if not to us?"

323
00:25:40,261 --> 00:25:44,004
"Do tell us then...
what husband do you want?"

324
00:25:44,084 --> 00:25:49,015
"Let me go!
Don't pester me"

325
00:25:50,028 --> 00:25:53,401
"How do I tell you
or explain this?"

326
00:25:53,941 --> 00:25:57,826
"My choice lies hidden
in my dreams"

327
00:26:07,223 --> 00:26:08,610
Congratulations on
your wedding!

328
00:26:09,849 --> 00:26:11,100
Greetings, Madam.
- Greetings.

329
00:26:11,348 --> 00:26:13,550
I have a small gift for you.

330
00:26:15,197 --> 00:26:18,445
Look at it through
my glasses...

331
00:26:18,525 --> 00:26:21,440
it's genuine gold.
- You are a jeweller.

332
00:26:21,672 --> 00:26:23,950
Who will bring gold,
if not you?

333
00:26:24,030 --> 00:26:26,319
I guessed the moment I saw
your wife...

334
00:26:26,399 --> 00:26:28,611
as to why you suddenly
agreed to the wedding.

335
00:26:28,691 --> 00:26:33,112
To be honest, I don't know how
my wife has approved of me!

336
00:26:41,723 --> 00:26:43,881
She's in Nirmal Village!

337
00:26:44,425 --> 00:26:46,888
A bride for you, as
beautiful as gold itself!

338
00:26:47,296 --> 00:26:48,740
She'll be my
daughter-in-law!

339
00:26:56,203 --> 00:26:58,860
Look at Harish!
Isn't he delighted?!

340
00:26:59,505 --> 00:27:02,808
People who don't marry, regret
it all their live, really!

341
00:27:03,131 --> 00:27:05,020
And those who marry
regret it even more!

342
00:27:06,095 --> 00:27:08,013
Oh, come on!
- I'm already regretting it.

343
00:27:09,093 --> 00:27:10,199
But I'm helpless.

344
00:27:11,050 --> 00:27:14,567
How would a poor goat
face a hungry tiger?

345
00:27:14,826 --> 00:27:16,893
Something wrong, Amit?
You hardly look happy.

346
00:27:17,134 --> 00:27:20,750
How'd I be happy especially since
I'm marrying a village-belle?

347
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:24,517
A village-belle,
do you get it?

348
00:27:24,675 --> 00:27:27,715
Tell me... how can I ever
bring a village-belle...

349
00:27:27,795 --> 00:27:30,007
to a gathering of this kind?

350
00:27:31,355 --> 00:27:33,468
You can always refuse.
Why get worked up?

351
00:27:34,071 --> 00:27:36,641
Refuse, eh?
Refuse my father?!

352
00:27:36,999 --> 00:27:39,078
You don't know my old man!

353
00:27:39,287 --> 00:27:41,011
He strides across like
an elephant...

354
00:27:41,222 --> 00:27:45,318
watches me like an owl
and roars like a lion!

355
00:27:46,184 --> 00:27:50,312
This liquor you're having
is a funny thing, Amit.

356
00:27:50,485 --> 00:27:54,038
Two extra drinks could
dwarf a giant!

357
00:27:54,886 --> 00:27:57,053
Have a couple of
quick ones then...

358
00:27:57,133 --> 00:27:58,482
and call it an attack
on your old man!

359
00:28:35,932 --> 00:28:37,219
What insolence is this?!

360
00:28:41,759 --> 00:28:44,841
This is a gun...
not insolence!

361
00:28:45,369 --> 00:28:49,064
It's loaded with six bullets
which will decide things!

362
00:28:49,144 --> 00:28:50,385
What nonsense are
you talking?

363
00:28:50,465 --> 00:28:52,666
Where've you picked up
that piece of junk from?

364
00:28:53,575 --> 00:28:55,247
You're the Junk-seller...

365
00:28:55,488 --> 00:28:58,039
who's saddling me with
all the unwanted things!

366
00:28:58,461 --> 00:29:00,438
You have called me
a junk-seller!

367
00:29:00,635 --> 00:29:03,227
Not even your grandpa
ever called me that!

368
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:05,856
You, son of my grandpa
in Heaven...

369
00:29:06,291 --> 00:29:08,533
prepare to leave
for heaven, too!

370
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:12,356
Are you going to kill me
with that toy-gun?

371
00:29:12,491 --> 00:29:14,191
You'll get a slap from me!

372
00:29:14,443 --> 00:29:17,504
This is no toy!
It's a real pistol!

373
00:29:24,533 --> 00:29:26,173
And this last bullet...

374
00:29:26,623 --> 00:29:28,401
will find my father's heart!

375
00:29:28,847 --> 00:29:30,738
Should you insist on this marriage...

376
00:29:30,881 --> 00:29:32,645
Go ahead and fire! But you
will marry that very girl!

377
00:29:32,725 --> 00:29:34,032
No way!
- Of course, you will!

378
00:29:34,273 --> 00:29:37,140
No!
- You will certainly!

379
00:29:45,659 --> 00:29:51,308
What have you done, Amit?
How could you do this?

380
00:29:51,563 --> 00:29:53,752
That which I should have
done long ago!

381
00:29:54,638 --> 00:29:57,628
Note down my last wish, Laxmi.

382
00:29:58,285 --> 00:30:00,908
That which must be followed.

383
00:30:01,444 --> 00:30:04,115
lf my last wish is
not adhered to...

384
00:30:04,493 --> 00:30:09,127
my soul will haunt this man
as a ghost, all his life!

385
00:30:10,223 --> 00:30:14,009
Don't say that!
Nothing will happen to you!

386
00:30:14,875 --> 00:30:18,169
Very well, Laxmi...
I must leave now.

387
00:30:19,943 --> 00:30:22,618
Forgive me for any wrong
I've done...

388
00:30:24,413 --> 00:30:28,108
I have a regret, though. 
I can't see my son getting married.

389
00:30:33,534 --> 00:30:36,456
Impossible! I can't do it!

390
00:30:37,308 --> 00:30:39,762
Looks like I'm surely
going to get married!

391
00:30:57,235 --> 00:30:58,565
Have you got it, teacher?

392
00:30:59,348 --> 00:31:02,240
I've looked for you all over,
and here you are.

393
00:31:04,762 --> 00:31:08,928
Wow! They look genuine!

394
00:31:09,394 --> 00:31:14,776
If man could help it, he'd even have
fake-men look like real!

395
00:31:16,655 --> 00:31:20,382
By the way, which drama are
you staging this festival?

396
00:31:20,648 --> 00:31:21,827
I'm playing Satyavan
Savitri.

397
00:31:21,907 --> 00:31:24,642
I'm going to wear these
ornaments and play the role.

398
00:31:24,722 --> 00:31:28,809
Are preparations for
Madhuri's wedding over?

399
00:31:29,324 --> 00:31:33,468
Should you need help from me,
please don't hesitate.

400
00:31:34,726 --> 00:31:38,633
What more than this
can you do, Teacher?

401
00:31:39,406 --> 00:31:41,500
I need God to help me now.

402
00:31:41,747 --> 00:31:42,925
Good-bye.

403
00:31:56,861 --> 00:31:59,483
Your bridegroom is here!

404
00:31:59,563 --> 00:32:01,954
It's considered auspicious to
see him before the wedding!

405
00:32:23,152 --> 00:32:26,783
Is the groom blind? He's wearing
dark-glasses even at night!

406
00:32:27,718 --> 00:32:32,230
He's had it, even before
he has set his eyes on her!

407
00:33:02,035 --> 00:33:04,421
Call the bride.
It's time for the vows.

408
00:33:13,626 --> 00:33:15,068
There she is!

409
00:34:56,863 --> 00:35:00,113
Stop showering petals on us!
This marriage will not take place!

410
00:35:00,555 --> 00:35:02,445
What nonsense are you talking?
The vows are over.

411
00:35:02,525 --> 00:35:06,189
No, father! This is no wedding.
It's a joke! A farce!

412
00:35:06,475 --> 00:35:09,782
Come to your senses! How can
you retract after the vows...

413
00:35:09,862 --> 00:35:12,479
Such a marriage cannot
be called a marriage, dad!

414
00:35:12,559 --> 00:35:13,771
Why not?

415
00:35:14,243 --> 00:35:19,352
You told me that girls from
the village are pure as gold.

416
00:35:19,733 --> 00:35:22,835
Then ask the village-belle, why
are they giving us fake gold?

417
00:35:25,527 --> 00:35:29,110
You have always worshipped
people from the villages, dad.

418
00:35:29,615 --> 00:35:31,235
But you can see
for yourself...

419
00:35:31,315 --> 00:35:34,835
how these people have taken
a gullible man for a ride!

420
00:35:35,411 --> 00:35:36,967
When the gold they
give us is fake...

421
00:35:37,498 --> 00:35:39,075
the bride must
be a fake, too!

422
00:35:41,069 --> 00:35:43,543
To be honest, I think
everything here...

423
00:35:43,623 --> 00:35:45,995
including her brother and
mother, appear to be fake!

424
00:35:46,334 --> 00:35:47,995
Especially the brother!

425
00:35:51,514 --> 00:35:55,039
Are the ornaments fake,
Shreekant?

426
00:36:03,410 --> 00:36:05,869
I'll explain this, my son!

427
00:36:06,448 --> 00:36:11,152
I joked with Shreekant that
I wanted 200 grams of gold.

428
00:36:12,404 --> 00:36:15,652
And that which is given
in a joke is always fake...

429
00:36:15,732 --> 00:36:16,936
not genuine!

430
00:36:17,374 --> 00:36:19,607
You have come to be a
professional joker, dad.

431
00:36:19,772 --> 00:36:22,944
In the process, you were about
to make a mockery of my life!

432
00:36:23,771 --> 00:36:25,803
But not anymore!

433
00:36:26,785 --> 00:36:29,080
Should these fake people
still appeal to you...

434
00:36:29,543 --> 00:36:32,350
you can take to them.

435
00:36:32,637 --> 00:36:34,333
You can indulge them
and the fake bride!

436
00:36:35,168 --> 00:36:37,825
Do as you please!
But I'm leaving now.

437
00:36:48,549 --> 00:36:51,547
Sir! Please save us
from ruination!

438
00:36:52,851 --> 00:36:54,680
God alone is the
saviour, son.

439
00:36:55,519 --> 00:36:58,286
But I have made a very
big mistake, too.

440
00:36:59,687 --> 00:37:00,911
I didn't know...

441
00:37:01,909 --> 00:37:05,127
that a small joke would
lead to such a calamity.

442
00:37:07,066 --> 00:37:10,589
That a spark could
ignite a raging fire!

443
00:37:13,037 --> 00:37:15,990
My son is a hot-blooded youth.

444
00:37:17,572 --> 00:37:19,306
It'll take him time
to cool down.

445
00:37:19,928 --> 00:37:21,680
But please don't worry.

446
00:37:22,185 --> 00:37:25,967
Very soon, I shall take
my daughter-in-law away...

447
00:37:26,381 --> 00:37:27,872
with all due ceremonies
and honour.

448
00:37:28,175 --> 00:37:30,700
This is my promise to you.
Good-bye.

449
00:37:43,070 --> 00:37:46,732
You've saved a friend today.
You've saved me from being ruined.

450
00:37:46,812 --> 00:37:49,609
That's okay. But I'm terribly
angry at your father.

451
00:37:49,689 --> 00:37:52,454
How could he decide anything
without his son's consent?

452
00:37:53,046 --> 00:37:54,737
I will decide things for
myself, in the future.

453
00:37:57,955 --> 00:37:59,222
You sinner!

454
00:38:00,547 --> 00:38:03,259
You have ruined your
sister's life!

455
00:38:05,010 --> 00:38:10,649
Hit me, mother!
I have sinned!

456
00:38:11,036 --> 00:38:13,007
I have ruined my
sister's life!

457
00:38:14,309 --> 00:38:19,160
No! Before you hit him,
you must realise...

458
00:38:19,843 --> 00:38:23,657
that he did it all
for my welfare.

459
00:38:24,154 --> 00:38:25,960
You must forgive him.

460
00:38:26,708 --> 00:38:29,841
There's no point in crying
or regretting anything now.

461
00:38:31,456 --> 00:38:34,679
A controversy which began
with fake-jewellery...

462
00:38:35,490 --> 00:38:38,241
eventually boiled down to
faces he didn't like.

463
00:38:39,877 --> 00:38:41,379
But don't worry, Mom.

464
00:38:42,460 --> 00:38:44,560
If there is sacred
anything in my marriage...

465
00:38:45,321 --> 00:38:48,069
it will break the shackles
of falsehoods...

466
00:38:48,433 --> 00:38:52,438
and help me settle down
with my husband one day!

467
00:40:14,674 --> 00:40:17,525
There are women waiting
for the interview, sir.

468
00:40:17,605 --> 00:40:19,038
Have all the ladies arrived?
- Yes, sir.

469
00:40:19,118 --> 00:40:20,938
I'll be there in a moment!

470
00:40:41,651 --> 00:40:43,401
My name is Kumar Chatterji.

471
00:40:43,481 --> 00:40:46,219
I happen to be the whole
and soul of the company...

472
00:40:46,299 --> 00:40:49,386
where nothing moves
without my permission!

473
00:40:49,466 --> 00:40:51,306
So you'd better give me...

474
00:40:51,386 --> 00:40:53,899
all the crucial information
about yourselves.

475
00:40:54,167 --> 00:40:59,990
My name is Manju Chaudhary.
I stay at Vakola, Santacruz.

476
00:41:08,651 --> 00:41:12,432
Have you come for the view...
I mean, for the interview?

477
00:41:12,928 --> 00:41:14,740
Yes.
- Please sit down.

478
00:41:15,065 --> 00:41:16,699
Sit here.

479
00:41:21,519 --> 00:41:26,323
Can you give me your contact number?
- Why?

480
00:41:26,403 --> 00:41:30,633
I might need it in
an emergency, you see!

481
00:41:33,765 --> 00:41:37,091
Let me land the job first.
The contact comes later.

482
00:41:37,645 --> 00:41:41,076
You can consider yourself employed!

483
00:41:48,899 --> 00:41:51,444
Who's the gentleman?
- Our boss!

484
00:41:51,524 --> 00:41:54,140
He's the one who will
interview all of you.

485
00:41:58,967 --> 00:42:01,432
This is Bhagat here.
- Yes, Mr Bhagat?

486
00:42:01,888 --> 00:42:05,633
I have decided to employ the
Minister's niece as the secretary.

487
00:42:05,713 --> 00:42:06,973
She will assume charge on Monday.

488
00:42:07,262 --> 00:42:09,949
But I've summoned many girls
for the interview, sir.

489
00:42:10,209 --> 00:42:13,126
What will I say to them?
- Do as you are told, Amit.

490
00:42:13,375 --> 00:42:15,865
This has to do with the
minister's niece.

491
00:42:24,540 --> 00:42:26,469
Have Kumar sent to me.

492
00:42:26,792 --> 00:42:28,878
It stops. And...

493
00:42:28,958 --> 00:42:32,188
Mr Kumar! The boss wants you inside.

494
00:42:32,268 --> 00:42:35,238
See? Nothing moves here
without my permission!

495
00:42:35,318 --> 00:42:37,244
Excuse me, I'll just be back.

496
00:42:40,913 --> 00:42:44,238
Did you send for me?
- Yes. Go and cancel the interviews.

497
00:42:45,043 --> 00:42:47,414
I get it! You must've got
a call from the M.D. !

498
00:42:47,494 --> 00:42:51,865
Sure. You're a smart guy!
Now go and call off the interviews.

499
00:42:51,945 --> 00:42:53,769
And see that none of them
takes offence.

500
00:42:53,849 --> 00:42:58,460
Don't worry, sir! I've called off
so many interviews... in the past!

501
00:43:08,632 --> 00:43:09,603
Ladies!

502
00:43:11,448 --> 00:43:13,630
I have bad news!

503
00:43:14,326 --> 00:43:18,098
My boss received a call
from his doctor just now.

504
00:43:18,899 --> 00:43:22,400
And that which he feared
has turned out to be true!

505
00:43:22,637 --> 00:43:24,069
What's wrong with him?

506
00:43:24,607 --> 00:43:27,486
He's suffering from
a cancer of the piles!

507
00:43:29,763 --> 00:43:31,751
Strange are God's ways!

508
00:43:32,104 --> 00:43:37,081
Such a tall and handsome man,
fair and broad-chested...

509
00:43:37,258 --> 00:43:41,289
suffering from cancer...
that too, of piles!

510
00:43:41,369 --> 00:43:43,276
Please convey our
best wishes to him!

511
00:43:43,524 --> 00:43:46,303
That's a contagious disease!
Let's return.

512
00:43:50,703 --> 00:43:52,314
Haven't you left, Madam.

513
00:43:53,281 --> 00:43:57,234
No, sir. Because I want
to rush you to the hospital.

514
00:43:57,811 --> 00:44:03,574
I'm sure it's you who has
the cancer, not your boss.

515
00:44:04,329 --> 00:44:08,417
Hats off to you, madam!
You're a smart one!

516
00:44:08,570 --> 00:44:10,458
But I'm no less.

517
00:44:10,538 --> 00:44:14,763
So let me tell you what
the man inside has cooked.

518
00:44:15,061 --> 00:44:18,158
Our boss received a call
from a superior...

519
00:44:18,238 --> 00:44:20,340
to employ someone
he favours.

520
00:44:20,420 --> 00:44:22,170
Which is why I had to
fake the illness.

521
00:44:22,549 --> 00:44:24,985
But you...
you're incomparable!

522
00:44:25,065 --> 00:44:28,412
But I promise to set you up
the moment I get the chance!

523
00:44:29,058 --> 00:44:31,060
You're an interesting
man, too.

524
00:44:51,078 --> 00:44:54,407
My name is Malti Chaudhary.
I came here for the interview.

525
00:44:54,781 --> 00:44:58,223
But your assistant said that
you're suffering from cancer.

526
00:44:58,303 --> 00:44:59,454
What?

527
00:44:59,749 --> 00:45:02,854
Cancer?! Who? Me?!
He's a bloody liar!

528
00:45:03,057 --> 00:45:06,835
Of course! All the girls prayed
for you, before they left.

529
00:45:07,373 --> 00:45:09,885
But I stayed back
to find out...

530
00:45:10,057 --> 00:45:12,105
the nature of the cancer
afflicting you.

531
00:45:12,344 --> 00:45:15,618
Is it the cancer of bribes?
Of employing a relative?

532
00:45:15,698 --> 00:45:17,826
Or is it the cancer
of influence?

533
00:45:18,037 --> 00:45:20,290
What exactly is the nature
of your cancer?

534
00:45:20,474 --> 00:45:22,937
You are accusing me.

535
00:45:25,514 --> 00:45:28,550
I will expose the truth behind
your so called interviews!

536
00:45:28,630 --> 00:45:31,216
I will take this story of
deceit to the newspapers!

537
00:45:31,497 --> 00:45:34,382
Let people know how
rich people like you...

538
00:45:34,462 --> 00:45:37,578
take advantage of
the deprived class!

539
00:45:38,473 --> 00:45:41,948
It's sad that I haven't even
got to tell you that...

540
00:45:42,028 --> 00:45:46,312
I've practiced hard to improve
my typing speed to 80 wpm.

541
00:45:46,392 --> 00:45:47,922
I have won a distinction
in shorthand...

542
00:45:48,002 --> 00:45:50,446
and I've topped in my course
of Secretarial Practice.

543
00:45:51,441 --> 00:45:53,236
But I will not spare you!

544
00:45:58,347 --> 00:46:02,605
Stop the girl who has walked
out of my office.

545
00:46:02,685 --> 00:46:03,968
And come inside immediately.

546
00:46:15,124 --> 00:46:19,689
Mr Bhagat? A girl just stormed
into my office.

547
00:46:19,769 --> 00:46:22,214
She has threatened to expose
us all in the newspapers.

548
00:46:22,821 --> 00:46:25,486
This thing about employing the
minister's niece...

549
00:46:25,566 --> 00:46:26,938
can give us a bad name.

550
00:46:27,372 --> 00:46:28,906
Okay. Thank you.

551
00:46:31,548 --> 00:46:33,589
Give the girl her
appointment letter.

552
00:46:34,750 --> 00:46:38,986
You're a great man, sir.
- And you're a cheap guy!

553
00:46:39,550 --> 00:46:44,869
If you lie ever again, you
will discover my greatness!

554
00:46:45,045 --> 00:46:47,421
You are a great man,
no doubt.

555
00:46:47,501 --> 00:46:49,567
But by employing the girl...

556
00:46:49,647 --> 00:46:54,081
you have driven away
my disappointment!

557
00:47:03,213 --> 00:47:04,860
You're done!
- What?!

558
00:47:04,940 --> 00:47:08,211
Naturally! With someone
like me for a fan....

559
00:47:08,291 --> 00:47:11,868
everything had to pale
into insignificance!

560
00:47:12,252 --> 00:47:15,483
After I lectured the
boss about you...

561
00:47:15,715 --> 00:47:17,859
he begged at my feet!

562
00:47:18,018 --> 00:47:19,706
Please employ her,
he said!

563
00:47:20,299 --> 00:47:23,150
And so... here's your
appointment letter.

564
00:47:28,195 --> 00:47:30,183
Listen... this is important.

565
00:47:30,263 --> 00:47:32,476
We will be working
together, no doubt.

566
00:47:32,556 --> 00:47:41,213
But if I may be able to help you
economically or physically...

567
00:47:41,293 --> 00:47:44,224
I'll be pleased to oblige,
and so will you!

568
00:47:44,304 --> 00:47:45,304
Pardon me?

569
00:47:46,836 --> 00:47:47,780
Very well.

570
00:47:51,392 --> 00:47:53,813
Very well indeed!

571
00:48:34,097 --> 00:48:37,280
Sister! How are you?
- I'm fine.

572
00:48:37,431 --> 00:48:38,760
Careful!

573
00:48:40,035 --> 00:48:41,167
How did it go?

574
00:48:42,015 --> 00:48:43,757
I'll tell you...
- What happened?

575
00:48:43,837 --> 00:48:46,695
Just what I wanted.
I have got the job.

576
00:48:46,775 --> 00:48:47,777
What?!

577
00:48:47,857 --> 00:48:50,721
Have you got a job as
his private secretary?!

578
00:48:50,918 --> 00:48:53,764
Yes!
- Didn't he recognise you?!

579
00:48:55,193 --> 00:48:59,518
No. He hasn't still got rid
of his dark-glasses.

580
00:49:01,369 --> 00:49:04,174
All this has happened
because of me, isn't it?

581
00:49:04,783 --> 00:49:07,587
Hadn't I done something
so foolish that day...

582
00:49:07,958 --> 00:49:12,690
you'd have been living
peacefully with your husband.

583
00:49:12,770 --> 00:49:15,079
Stop cribbing and crying!

584
00:49:15,682 --> 00:49:18,093
All you did was to care for
your sister's well-being!

585
00:49:18,639 --> 00:49:21,358
I need your help right now.

586
00:49:22,222 --> 00:49:25,470
I can't succeed in this
drama without your help.

587
00:49:26,394 --> 00:49:27,466
You will help me, won't you?

588
00:49:27,546 --> 00:49:32,566
I'd do more than laying
down my life for you, sis.

589
00:49:34,010 --> 00:49:36,236
It won't come to that,
God-willing.

590
00:49:40,152 --> 00:49:44,779
Look at Madhuri going!
- She's got the city airs!

591
00:49:44,859 --> 00:49:47,463
The high-heeled sandals,
the swaying gait...

592
00:49:47,543 --> 00:49:49,575
And look carefully!

593
00:49:49,655 --> 00:49:52,302
She has even wiped out the
matrimonial vermillion!

594
00:49:52,382 --> 00:49:55,056
There's no dearth of
vermillion in Bombay...

595
00:49:55,136 --> 00:49:57,273
nor that of people who'd
be interested in her!

596
00:49:57,353 --> 00:49:59,635
Look at her ways!

597
00:50:01,171 --> 00:50:02,931
The Bombay-bird indeed!

598
00:50:08,808 --> 00:50:10,014
Have some tea, dear.

599
00:50:20,949 --> 00:50:22,568
Why are you looking
at me like this, mom?

600
00:50:23,131 --> 00:50:24,495
It's nothing, dear.

601
00:50:26,844 --> 00:50:31,393
I know what you have to go
through, for my sake, mom.

602
00:50:31,886 --> 00:50:33,627
You have to put up
with a lot of jibes.

603
00:50:33,707 --> 00:50:38,168
How far have you gone away
from our culture, Madhuri?

604
00:50:39,847 --> 00:50:43,447
You have even wiped away
the matrimonial vermillion!

605
00:50:46,948 --> 00:50:49,675
Of what use is
the vermillion...

606
00:50:50,150 --> 00:50:52,250
that returned after
reaching my forehead?

607
00:50:52,596 --> 00:50:55,218
If there is any strength in
my belief of my marriage...

608
00:50:55,455 --> 00:50:57,990
the vermillion will return
to my forehead one day!

609
00:51:03,085 --> 00:51:07,142
Your son-in-law is the
boss of the company...

610
00:51:07,869 --> 00:51:10,372
where I've been employed.

611
00:51:10,769 --> 00:51:14,363
Really? Hasn't he
recognised you, then?

612
00:51:15,372 --> 00:51:18,172
No. He's just been
introduced to me.

613
00:51:18,937 --> 00:51:20,815
He'll get to know
me very soon, too.

614
00:51:22,429 --> 00:51:25,063
I only need
your blessings now.

615
00:51:26,665 --> 00:51:30,827
O Goddess Mother! Just as You can be
pleased and angry with your devotees...

616
00:51:31,205 --> 00:51:33,549
Your devotees have the
right to...

617
00:51:33,972 --> 00:51:36,570
be angry and happy
with You, too.

618
00:51:37,141 --> 00:51:40,778
I'm terribly angry with You
for what You've done to us!

619
00:51:41,436 --> 00:51:43,172
My son has been married...

620
00:51:43,493 --> 00:51:45,285
but my daughter-in-law
hasn't come home!

621
00:51:45,365 --> 00:51:47,373
I will not pray to You
till such time...

622
00:51:47,718 --> 00:51:50,400
as Madhuri comes here
as my daughter-in-law!

623
00:52:15,076 --> 00:52:17,017
Do come...

624
00:52:23,248 --> 00:52:26,260
Have you never been in love?

625
00:52:26,732 --> 00:52:29,758
I want a rose with fragrance and
you bring me one that stinks!

626
00:52:29,838 --> 00:52:31,566
D'you want one that has
more fragrance than this?

627
00:52:32,116 --> 00:52:35,028
I'll get it for you.
But do talk to me!

628
00:52:35,108 --> 00:52:36,923
Sure... No!

629
00:52:37,166 --> 00:52:40,007
Go outside and attend to
the forward and backward... - What?

630
00:52:40,087 --> 00:52:41,494
I mean, the inward and
outward correspondence!

631
00:52:41,574 --> 00:52:44,671
That's what I'm always doing!
What a bore!

632
00:53:10,800 --> 00:53:14,908
How often have I told you
not to call me Uncle ?

633
00:53:15,894 --> 00:53:19,862
What do I call an uncle,
if not Uncle?

634
00:53:19,942 --> 00:53:24,199
Don't you try to act
smart with me...!

635
00:53:24,279 --> 00:53:26,714
And if you must really
call someone uncle...

636
00:53:26,794 --> 00:53:29,009
you can always call
Anthony that!

637
00:53:33,463 --> 00:53:35,309
The score's 30
for no loss, sir!

638
00:53:39,480 --> 00:53:43,245
What was he saying?
- He asked me to call you uncle!

639
00:53:47,169 --> 00:53:52,555
I always steal a rose from
the neighbour's garden...

640
00:53:53,074 --> 00:53:56,903
brave the ferocious dog there
and bring it to you!

641
00:53:58,663 --> 00:54:00,005
It's beautiful, isn't it?

642
00:54:00,506 --> 00:54:03,265
But although I have presented
you with 25 roses...

643
00:54:03,871 --> 00:54:06,585
I have still to win over
your heart!

644
00:54:12,027 --> 00:54:13,848
I always spray a perfume
on it...

645
00:54:14,103 --> 00:54:16,030
so its fragrance
never wears off.

646
00:54:16,904 --> 00:54:22,154
But alas! The fragrance
of my love...

647
00:54:22,542 --> 00:54:24,716
never reaches your
beautiful nose!

648
00:55:34,703 --> 00:55:37,567
That's a beautiful rose!
- Isn't it?

649
00:55:37,820 --> 00:55:39,887
Who brought it?
- I did.

650
00:55:40,594 --> 00:55:41,952
It's a strange thing,
isn't it...

651
00:55:42,163 --> 00:55:44,960
that the rose always smells
of different perfumes.

652
00:55:45,387 --> 00:55:52,003
Brut, Charlie, Sex Appeal,
Henna...

653
00:55:52,278 --> 00:55:55,553
Henna? That's right!

654
00:55:55,888 --> 00:55:59,540
I love roses!
So does my mother.

655
00:55:59,620 --> 00:56:02,970
And she'd love to meet you.

656
00:56:03,050 --> 00:56:05,839
So why don't you come over
to my place next Sunday?

657
00:56:05,919 --> 00:56:08,764
But don't tell Boss
about it.

658
00:56:09,149 --> 00:56:13,420
He's a good man.
But he's dull and boring.

659
00:56:13,500 --> 00:56:15,897
He knows nothing of romance
and wouldn't understand this!

660
00:56:20,756 --> 00:56:23,019
We have an urgent meeting to attend.
- Go ahead, sir.

661
00:56:23,099 --> 00:56:24,909
You will come along, too!
- I?

662
00:56:24,989 --> 00:56:26,189
Come on!

663
00:56:34,996 --> 00:56:36,748
The lady is here, sir.

664
00:56:42,921 --> 00:56:44,118
I'm going out.

665
00:56:44,533 --> 00:56:47,531
There are some papers in the
file which I want you to type.

666
00:56:48,766 --> 00:56:49,772
There's another thing.

667
00:56:49,949 --> 00:56:51,382
I'm happy with your work.

668
00:56:52,272 --> 00:56:54,842
But you'd better not waste
time in unnecessary things.

669
00:58:28,334 --> 00:58:30,838
I'm sorry, but I didn't
notice you coming.

670
00:58:30,918 --> 00:58:33,778
How would you? You were busy
admiring the photograph.

671
00:58:34,147 --> 00:58:35,769
Is that your boyfriend?

672
00:58:39,214 --> 00:58:42,423
He's a boy, all right.
But he's still not a friend.

673
00:58:43,674 --> 00:58:44,730
He's my boss, actually.

674
00:58:44,810 --> 00:58:46,620
It's a cakewalk for you,
in that case!

675
00:58:48,104 --> 00:58:51,263
Men are usually
very careless.

676
00:58:51,874 --> 00:58:56,039
If they find someone taking
proper care of them...

677
00:58:56,119 --> 00:58:59,003
they could even make
good husbands!

678
00:58:59,793 --> 00:59:02,194
In any case, a beautiful
girl like you...

679
00:59:02,280 --> 00:59:05,575
can be had only by a very
fortunate man!

680
00:59:06,419 --> 00:59:10,943
Here's your rent.

681
00:59:12,574 --> 00:59:15,068
Mark my words.

682
00:59:15,531 --> 00:59:18,852
This boss will one day
be a slave to you!

683
00:59:18,932 --> 00:59:20,428
Just you watch!

684
00:59:23,061 --> 00:59:24,868
Care for some tea?

685
00:59:25,401 --> 00:59:27,696
Don't bother about bringing it.
I'll fetch it myself!

686
00:59:28,850 --> 00:59:30,159
Here's a set of
handkerchiefs, sis.

687
00:59:30,239 --> 00:59:32,539
I've bought them with the
salary I've received.

688
00:59:34,181 --> 00:59:35,499
Tell me something.

689
00:59:35,862 --> 00:59:38,677
You're normally scolding me
for being careless...

690
00:59:38,757 --> 00:59:41,028
and not looking
after my things.

691
00:59:41,326 --> 00:59:45,053
But where have you lost
your hanky today?

692
01:00:35,301 --> 01:00:37,154
Have you sent for me, sir?
- Yes.

693
01:00:37,641 --> 01:00:39,797
I wanted to thank you.
Do sit down.

694
01:00:39,877 --> 01:00:41,556
May I fetch a pad if you
want to dictate a letter?

695
01:00:45,621 --> 01:00:47,996
Have you ever met
a careless man?

696
01:00:48,559 --> 01:00:51,190
What? Oh yes, I have...
I'm meeting one right now.

697
01:00:51,270 --> 01:00:53,383
Me, you mean?

698
01:00:53,609 --> 01:00:56,680
I wonder when I'll
stop being so careless.

699
01:00:56,760 --> 01:00:59,767
You have considered my cabin
as your own...

700
01:00:59,847 --> 01:01:02,085
and cleaned out all the mess.

701
01:01:04,871 --> 01:01:09,464
But your carelessness can
lead to a setback.

702
01:01:10,124 --> 01:01:13,738
You could lose something
precious, out of carelessness.

703
01:01:13,818 --> 01:01:15,614
Won't that be a pity?

704
01:01:16,281 --> 01:01:19,553
Your cabin was in bad shape.
Especially your files.

705
01:01:19,633 --> 01:01:21,638
I remembered it from my
very first day here.

706
01:01:21,718 --> 01:01:23,685
No matter what you
remember...

707
01:01:23,765 --> 01:01:25,614
but you also have
a very bad memory.

708
01:01:25,984 --> 01:01:27,109
Pardon me?

709
01:01:27,558 --> 01:01:32,282
You've forgotten something, too.
- Have you remembered it then?

710
01:01:32,669 --> 01:01:36,267
Naturally. How can I forget
something I possess?

711
01:01:38,607 --> 01:01:40,428
What are you staring
at me for?

712
01:01:40,508 --> 01:01:45,390
It's the handkerchief
that you forgot!

713
01:01:48,109 --> 01:01:49,495
Excuse me...
- Yes?

714
01:01:49,575 --> 01:01:52,060
You're participating in the
badminton matches this time.

715
01:01:52,140 --> 01:01:53,545
Why don't we have
a match, too?

716
01:01:56,307 --> 01:01:59,278
I always lose miserably,
while you're a champion.

717
01:01:59,728 --> 01:02:01,294
Who told you that I am a champion?

718
01:02:01,514 --> 01:02:02,926
Everybody in the office knows it.

719
01:02:03,006 --> 01:02:06,284
Okay. But one who wins
can always lose...

720
01:02:06,364 --> 01:02:07,714
and the loser might
even win a game.

721
01:02:07,794 --> 01:02:10,433
Let's a question of playing and
you must have a match with me.

722
01:02:12,035 --> 01:02:14,085
You can consider me game.

723
01:02:27,080 --> 01:02:29,588
You?! What are you
doing here?

724
01:02:30,204 --> 01:02:33,776
Funny! But I was about to ask
you the same question.

725
01:02:34,145 --> 01:02:36,883
Are you to here to
make a match with someone?

726
01:02:36,963 --> 01:02:39,791
Not to make a match...
but to play one!

727
01:02:40,030 --> 01:02:42,548
Am I not a loyal man, sir?

728
01:02:42,628 --> 01:02:46,784
I've come all the way to
watch you play goodminton !

729
01:02:47,452 --> 01:02:49,370
Goodminton? What on earth is that?

730
01:02:49,997 --> 01:02:52,697
When a super-player like
you plays bad-minton...

731
01:02:52,777 --> 01:02:54,981
it's bound to earn the
name of good-minton !

732
01:02:59,133 --> 01:03:00,473
Welcome, Ms Malti!

733
01:03:00,739 --> 01:03:02,980
The shuttlecock is here!

734
01:03:03,060 --> 01:03:05,536
Get cracking, sir!

735
01:03:09,599 --> 01:03:12,148
What are you doing here?
- I came here for the fragrance.

736
01:03:12,228 --> 01:03:15,370
But since you are here, you bring
the spring with you!

737
01:03:15,450 --> 01:03:17,316
Should we start the game?

738
01:03:17,590 --> 01:03:19,994
What d'you think, Mr Kumar?
Should we start?

739
01:03:20,074 --> 01:03:24,523
Why are you asking him?!
- Get cracking, the two of you!

740
01:03:24,603 --> 01:03:28,001
The ideal moment of the day!

741
01:03:28,081 --> 01:03:31,324
Get, set and go!

742
01:03:32,990 --> 01:03:36,018
How'd he get here?
- I wouldn't know!

743
01:03:37,346 --> 01:03:40,927
Who's into service, sir?
- Service?

744
01:03:41,007 --> 01:03:42,816
Who'll serve first?

745
01:03:46,504 --> 01:03:47,903
Let's get started!

746
01:04:27,815 --> 01:04:30,851
You've lost a love-game!

747
01:04:30,931 --> 01:04:33,705
Oh no! He's the champ.

748
01:04:33,913 --> 01:04:35,867
He lost because
he wanted me to win.

749
01:04:35,947 --> 01:04:40,775
You have a heart then?
I wear it on my sleeve!

750
01:04:40,986 --> 01:04:44,726
Keep your promise now and
treat us to some Chinese food.

751
01:04:44,806 --> 01:04:46,062
That's a good idea!
Let's go.

752
01:04:46,142 --> 01:04:49,184
But you don't eat Chinese
food, do you?

753
01:04:49,264 --> 01:04:52,047
How about your allergy?

754
01:04:52,466 --> 01:04:54,478
Anyway, thanks for the game.
I must leave now.

755
01:04:54,854 --> 01:04:56,857
Keep this, sir.
You can play with it!

756
01:05:00,006 --> 01:05:02,558
It's good that you
called me over, madam.

757
01:05:02,638 --> 01:05:05,619
Or they use badminton
as an excuse for rape!

758
01:05:05,699 --> 01:05:08,956
The other day, a sixty-year
old woman was lured...

759
01:05:48,260 --> 01:05:52,685
Why did you plant the
cauliflower in my cabin?

760
01:05:52,918 --> 01:05:55,960
The roses are always passed
on to the other girl!

761
01:05:56,297 --> 01:06:00,499
You can have this cauliflower
and give her some, too!

762
01:06:00,852 --> 01:06:03,092
If I had to give her
vegetables, why would...

763
01:06:03,172 --> 01:06:05,079
I give her a cauliflower?

764
01:06:05,159 --> 01:06:08,833
I could give her bananas,
bitter-gourd or anything!

765
01:06:10,346 --> 01:06:13,259
Give anything you wish!
To hell with it!

766
01:06:14,314 --> 01:06:15,939
I wonder where
they come from!

767
01:06:17,288 --> 01:06:18,373
Come in.

768
01:06:19,505 --> 01:06:20,933
The score is 340 runs for
9 wickets, sir.

769
01:06:21,013 --> 01:06:24,169
Did I ask you for the score?
Go and fetch me a flower.

770
01:06:24,249 --> 01:06:27,559
What file, sir?
- Not file! A flower! A rose!

771
01:06:27,639 --> 01:06:29,853
What colour?
- A red one will do!

772
01:06:29,933 --> 01:06:32,653
One like your cheek...
No! Like mine!

773
01:06:33,161 --> 01:06:34,580
Here's the money.
Hurry up.

774
01:06:38,243 --> 01:06:40,723
I'll personally give her
a rose today.

775
01:06:43,692 --> 01:06:45,707
Welcome, Mr Kumar.

776
01:06:45,892 --> 01:06:47,649
What perfume does your
rose have today?

777
01:06:48,295 --> 01:06:50,648
But this is the first time
I've brought you a rose!

778
01:06:52,701 --> 01:06:55,542
Now look; you bring me
a rose everyday.

779
01:06:55,885 --> 01:06:59,757
Why don't you admit that?
I haven't turned it down, have I?

780
01:07:00,767 --> 01:07:03,819
Yes, I bring one everyday.
You like roses, don't you?

781
01:07:03,899 --> 01:07:07,609
Yes. I love them. Where do you
bring such beautiful roses from?

782
01:07:07,769 --> 01:07:09,810
I steal them!
- Speak softly!

783
01:07:09,890 --> 01:07:10,355
Why?

784
01:07:10,435 --> 01:07:13,610
What if someone hears you?
- I'm not scared of anyone!

785
01:07:13,690 --> 01:07:15,528
But I'm scared.
- Of whom?

786
01:07:15,718 --> 01:07:16,439
The boss, of course.

787
01:07:16,519 --> 01:07:18,533
The boss?

788
01:07:20,530 --> 01:07:24,448
Tell you what? Put the
rose in my hair...

789
01:07:24,528 --> 01:07:27,346
and return to your cabin.
Okay?

790
01:07:40,640 --> 01:07:44,511
When will you meet me again?

791
01:07:46,032 --> 01:07:49,225
Tonight?
- Tonight?! Where is that?

792
01:07:49,305 --> 01:07:52,806
In your dreams.
- Dreams?

793
01:07:53,179 --> 01:07:55,119
Wonderful! That's the best place!

794
01:07:55,199 --> 01:07:57,494
Neither will the evil
boss hound us...

795
01:07:57,574 --> 01:07:59,214
nor will the fat girl
be around!

796
01:07:59,294 --> 01:08:02,341
Just you and me...
just the two of us!

797
01:08:08,637 --> 01:08:10,555
Sit down, Mr Kumar.

798
01:08:11,496 --> 01:08:13,505
I've got to ask you some
important questions.

799
01:08:14,144 --> 01:08:17,074
I've already put in 10 years
of service in this company.

800
01:08:17,159 --> 01:08:19,019
Do you intend to interview me
all over again?

801
01:08:19,099 --> 01:08:20,700
Yes. You could say that.

802
01:08:20,964 --> 01:08:24,552
How many branches do we
have all over the country?

803
01:08:25,023 --> 01:08:26,392
22 branches.
- We have 23.

804
01:08:27,076 --> 01:08:29,831
We are starting a new branch
on the Nicobar Islands.

805
01:08:30,289 --> 01:08:34,318
You mean, the one called
Andaman and Nicobar Islands?

806
01:08:34,398 --> 01:08:35,974
Fantastic! Congratulations!

807
01:08:36,054 --> 01:08:38,641
Ever since you've joined the
systems and communications...

808
01:08:38,721 --> 01:08:40,336
our company is making
great progress!

809
01:08:41,222 --> 01:08:44,500
Congratulations to you, too.
- Thank you. But what for?

810
01:08:44,824 --> 01:08:46,495
You have been given
a promotion.

811
01:08:47,199 --> 01:08:49,996
Have I? Thank you very much.

812
01:08:50,959 --> 01:08:54,356
You are being appointed
manager of the new branch.

813
01:08:55,813 --> 01:08:58,457
The new branch at
Nicobar?

814
01:08:58,655 --> 01:09:01,163
You mean, I'll have
to go there?!

815
01:09:01,243 --> 01:09:03,640
We need a responsible
man there.

816
01:09:03,831 --> 01:09:05,967
And who could be more
responsible than you are?

817
01:09:06,151 --> 01:09:08,472
You have been
misinformed, sir!

818
01:09:08,552 --> 01:09:11,409
I am the most irresponsible man in
the organisation! It's the truth!

819
01:09:11,489 --> 01:09:12,939
How can you say that?

820
01:09:13,143 --> 01:09:14,902
Although our office opens
at 10.00...

821
01:09:15,518 --> 01:09:17,823
you usually walked in
at 11 or 11.30 a.m.

822
01:09:18,016 --> 01:09:19,915
But nowadays, you are here
on the dot at 9.30 a.m.!

823
01:09:20,223 --> 01:09:22,299
That too, with
a rose in hand!

824
01:09:22,695 --> 01:09:27,657
You've worked wonders with our
systems and communications!

825
01:09:29,100 --> 01:09:33,496
But isn't Nicobar Island
very far away, sir?

826
01:09:33,913 --> 01:09:36,641
That's okay. You won't
be swimming across anyway.

827
01:09:36,721 --> 01:09:38,039
We'll give you an
air-ticket instead.

828
01:09:38,321 --> 01:09:40,424
Even out there, you will
have no real problems.

829
01:09:40,767 --> 01:09:42,967
Although you will not
find any roses around...

830
01:09:43,047 --> 01:09:44,691
there are girls aplenty.

831
01:09:44,946 --> 01:09:47,814
Of the man-eating variety!

832
01:09:52,071 --> 01:09:54,737
I'd gladly be a peon
in this office!

833
01:09:54,992 --> 01:09:57,139
But please don't banish me
to Nicobar, sir!

834
01:09:57,618 --> 01:10:00,095
I'll be ruined, sir!

835
01:10:00,464 --> 01:10:03,228
There's a condition.
...No more roses!

836
01:10:13,124 --> 01:10:14,016
Malti?

837
01:10:16,971 --> 01:10:18,351
Sit down.

838
01:10:19,785 --> 01:10:21,360
Let's begin with
the dictation.

839
01:10:28,707 --> 01:10:30,616
What was he doing to you
behind the glass-panel?

840
01:10:32,420 --> 01:10:36,044
He was putting a rose
in my hair, sir.

841
01:10:36,203 --> 01:10:38,173
A rose? I see!

842
01:10:44,555 --> 01:10:47,270
I've written that, sir.
- Really? Let's proceed...

843
01:10:48,062 --> 01:10:50,596
Did he cuddle up to you
in the cab?

844
01:10:52,285 --> 01:10:53,376
Yes.

845
01:11:00,405 --> 01:11:03,605
What else did he do to you
in the cab? Did he talk a lot?

846
01:11:04,245 --> 01:11:06,954
Yes, he did.

847
01:11:07,355 --> 01:11:10,602
He told me that I look very
beautiful in a pink sari.

848
01:11:10,968 --> 01:11:13,205
He's right!
You do look beautiful!

849
01:11:21,803 --> 01:11:23,382
How far did he take you
in the cab?

850
01:11:24,445 --> 01:11:27,525
Far... far away.
-Very far.

851
01:11:28,045 --> 01:11:31,598
He wanted to take me home
to meet his mother.

852
01:11:33,119 --> 01:11:35,205
He has no parents!
They are dead!

853
01:11:35,511 --> 01:11:38,492
That's how he lures gullible
girls into visiting his house!

854
01:11:39,954 --> 01:11:43,129
And then... have you seen
the film Insaaf Ka Tarazu?

855
01:11:43,789 --> 01:11:45,285
Yes, I have. So?

856
01:11:45,452 --> 01:11:50,854
So it's... rape...
twice in succession!

857
01:11:52,492 --> 01:11:54,599
And then?
- It's the Courts!

858
01:12:03,611 --> 01:12:04,869
But I've already jotted
that down, sir.

859
01:12:20,972 --> 01:12:22,309
You will have to
concede my request.

860
01:12:22,389 --> 01:12:25,092
My mother has sent some
special food for you.

861
01:12:25,769 --> 01:12:26,971
Your mother has?
- That's right.

862
01:12:27,051 --> 01:12:29,399
She's a great cook!
Check it out for yourself!

863
01:12:30,335 --> 01:12:32,131
I don't doubt that.
But...

864
01:12:33,027 --> 01:12:34,251
Has someone poisoned
your ears against me?

865
01:12:34,331 --> 01:12:36,291
No...

866
01:12:36,371 --> 01:12:39,731
In that case, you must
try the food.

867
01:12:39,811 --> 01:12:43,049
That's a request from me
as well as my mother!

868
01:12:53,490 --> 01:12:54,611
Sit down.

869
01:13:03,964 --> 01:13:07,201
What will you have?
- Anything you wish.

870
01:13:09,854 --> 01:13:11,209
How's the restaurant?

871
01:13:15,118 --> 01:13:16,592
You choose the menu today.

872
01:13:19,405 --> 01:13:22,358
A vegetable-rice, a steamed
potato-dish...

873
01:13:22,966 --> 01:13:28,284
a radish-pancake, and
a seasoned lentil-curry.

874
01:13:30,766 --> 01:13:32,084
Listen...
- Yes.

875
01:13:32,526 --> 01:13:35,416
Also include a dish
of bitter-gourd.

876
01:13:36,889 --> 01:13:38,189
Something wrong?

877
01:13:38,859 --> 01:13:43,037
Except for the bitter-gourd,
we have common tastes!

878
01:13:46,366 --> 01:13:49,492
Do you know, when I saw you
for the first time...

879
01:13:50,834 --> 01:13:53,008
Where was that?
- At the interview, of course.

880
01:13:53,843 --> 01:13:59,413
I had a feeling that I had
met you somewhere.

881
01:14:00,209 --> 01:14:03,398
Where could that be?
- In my dreams, perhaps.

882
01:14:04,541 --> 01:14:07,823
You could really
have met me earlier...

883
01:14:07,903 --> 01:14:11,875
and forgotten me like
a bad dream?

884
01:14:13,164 --> 01:14:16,217
Perhaps. But I won't
ever forget you now.

885
01:14:21,971 --> 01:14:23,914
What are you doing?
Won't you eat?

886
01:14:23,994 --> 01:14:25,305
You finish your food first.

887
01:14:25,385 --> 01:14:27,233
That's the worst thing
about Hindu women!

888
01:14:27,313 --> 01:14:29,992
Like my mother, for instance.
They serve others first...

889
01:14:30,072 --> 01:14:31,964
and themselves eat later.
That's not fair.

890
01:14:32,967 --> 01:14:34,474
Who else do you have
in the family?

891
01:14:34,554 --> 01:14:37,145
It's just my parents and me.
- Is that all?

892
01:14:37,523 --> 01:14:40,762
Why? Must I have more?

893
01:14:42,708 --> 01:14:46,083
I see what you are
getting at. But, no...

894
01:14:53,070 --> 01:14:57,012
I'm surprised that even after
so many years in England...

895
01:14:57,425 --> 01:14:59,404
you still haven't forgotten
your old customs.

896
01:15:00,531 --> 01:15:02,613
I haven't forgotten
anything, except...

897
01:15:03,077 --> 01:15:05,202
for some terrible memories
that I want to forget.

898
01:15:41,837 --> 01:15:45,214
Thank you, O Lord!

899
01:15:45,579 --> 01:15:47,215
Did you see that?
- See what?

900
01:15:47,659 --> 01:15:49,579
Amit has been whistling!

901
01:15:50,459 --> 01:15:54,628
It's a whistle of joy
and happiness...

902
01:15:54,963 --> 01:15:56,978
that which spells melody!

903
01:15:57,274 --> 01:16:00,235
It's after 2 years that
Amit has whistled again!

904
01:16:00,939 --> 01:16:04,459
Do you understand?
- No, I don't. Please explain.

905
01:16:05,557 --> 01:16:07,297
You're an ignorant man.

906
01:16:07,747 --> 01:16:11,732
Don't you remember Amit
whistling all the while...

907
01:16:11,812 --> 01:16:13,729
even as he walked,
talked and ate?

908
01:16:14,935 --> 01:16:18,045
Since the wedding, however, he
forgot his favourite whistle.

909
01:16:18,612 --> 01:16:20,596
And he has been
whistling today!

910
01:16:20,837 --> 01:16:23,394
Which means he is
truly delighted!

911
01:16:23,691 --> 01:16:25,442
This is when I must
talk to him...

912
01:16:25,522 --> 01:16:28,595
about bringing our
daughter-in-law home!

913
01:16:33,220 --> 01:16:35,823
My son...
- Yes, Mom?

914
01:16:36,378 --> 01:16:39,578
I'm delighted to see
you happy today.

915
01:16:40,257 --> 01:16:43,785
On this happy occasion then,
I've something to say to you.

916
01:16:44,040 --> 01:16:47,911
Sure. Go ahead, Mom.
- Can we bring Madhuri home?

917
01:16:48,302 --> 01:16:50,901
I've forgotten the past.

918
01:16:51,174 --> 01:16:52,963
I can't be blamed if it
continues to haunt you.

919
01:16:53,043 --> 01:16:55,948
It isn't my fault either for
remembering the past.

920
01:16:56,493 --> 01:16:59,508
I can't help it, if you
have a bad memory.

921
01:17:04,529 --> 01:17:05,649
Do you get the point?

922
01:17:06,920 --> 01:17:09,189
When a young man whistles
after a gap of 2 years...

923
01:17:09,481 --> 01:17:11,383
