Greetings, brother-in-law!

994
01:25:49,142 --> 01:25:52,854
Now tell me what would we have,
if not the Himalayas?

995
01:25:52,934 --> 01:25:54,130
Himalayas, my foot!

996
01:25:54,210 --> 01:25:56,087
And keep standing!
Don't sit down!

997
01:25:56,778 --> 01:25:58,405
Are not well?
- I've caught a cold.

998
01:25:58,485 --> 01:25:59,549
You shouldn't be shouting.

999
01:25:59,629 --> 01:26:03,112
I wanted to know when you're taking
my sister away, brother-in-law.

1000
01:26:03,481 --> 01:26:06,350
To begin with, stop
calling me brother-in-law!

1001
01:26:06,430 --> 01:26:08,443
Okay, brother-in-law...
- There you go again!

1002
01:26:08,523 --> 01:26:11,363
I've come to you with hopes,
brother-in-law.

1003
01:26:11,443 --> 01:26:15,078
I thought I'd meet you and
have a chat with you!

1004
01:26:15,158 --> 01:26:17,210
That I'd have something
to drink!

1005
01:26:17,858 --> 01:26:19,554
But never mind...

1006
01:26:19,634 --> 01:26:23,517
I'll go and show these
pictures to your parents.

1007
01:26:25,496 --> 01:26:27,438
There's no point in tearing
them! I have the negatives!

1008
01:26:27,785 --> 01:26:30,512
Do you think you can
blackmail me with this?

1009
01:26:30,675 --> 01:26:32,956
Go ahead and show them to
my parents! I don't care!

1010
01:26:33,271 --> 01:26:37,257
Sure, I'll go away. But
I won't stop tailing you!

1011
01:26:37,337 --> 01:26:38,889
Not there! This way out!

1012
01:26:48,933 --> 01:26:50,836
I have learnt something
absolutely explosive!

1013
01:26:51,312 --> 01:26:53,143
Really? What is it?

1014
01:26:53,603 --> 01:26:55,155
I will tell you
when the time comes.

1015
01:26:55,345 --> 01:26:57,255
Whom is it about?

1016
01:26:57,989 --> 01:27:01,887
It's about the boss,
Mr Amit Chaudhary.

1017
01:27:04,878 --> 01:27:08,144
But I will tell you only
when the time comes!

1018
01:27:10,790 --> 01:27:11,924
The right time, my foot!

1019
01:27:22,803 --> 01:27:24,706
What's wrong?
Aren't you well?

1020
01:27:24,786 --> 01:27:26,676
I think I have a fever.

1021
01:27:26,756 --> 01:27:28,384
You're running
a high temperature.

1022
01:27:30,891 --> 01:27:32,501
Come on, get up.
- Yes madam.

1023
01:27:33,231 --> 01:27:34,421
Take this bag away.

1024
01:27:35,316 --> 01:27:37,639
Go home and relax.
- Who'll complete my work?

1025
01:27:37,719 --> 01:27:39,793
I will.
- Okay.

1026
01:27:40,498 --> 01:27:42,741
But call me at home, if
you have any problems.

1027
01:27:59,459 --> 01:28:01,992
Who is this girl?

1028
01:28:02,300 --> 01:28:04,165
That's precisely what
I want to ask you.

1029
01:28:04,578 --> 01:28:07,614
I hope you haven't got
your son married again!

1030
01:28:07,965 --> 01:28:09,936
What do you mean?
- I mean...

1031
01:28:10,016 --> 01:28:14,815
this girl was clinging
to your son as if she were his wife!

1032
01:28:15,329 --> 01:28:16,751
What are you talking about?

1033
01:28:16,831 --> 01:28:18,601
They were having a ball
in the seas...

1034
01:28:18,681 --> 01:28:21,734
and were even singing
a duet!

1035
01:28:22,015 --> 01:28:23,774
We meet on the sly,
away from prying eyes

1036
01:28:23,854 --> 01:28:26,123
We're afraid, someone
might see us

1037
01:28:29,187 --> 01:28:32,681
You should be ashamed
to accuse my son!

1038
01:28:34,201 --> 01:28:35,829
Although you are visiting
us after a long time...

1039
01:28:36,163 --> 01:28:38,786
I will not enquire
after your health!

1040
01:28:38,866 --> 01:28:41,081
But I want to know what
insolent behaviour is this?

1041
01:28:41,301 --> 01:28:44,687
I will not tell you about
my welfare either.

1042
01:28:44,864 --> 01:28:46,385
And this is no insolence!

1043
01:28:46,465 --> 01:28:50,428
I've taken pictures
to back my claim!

1044
01:28:51,107 --> 01:28:52,844
It's Amit.
- Of course.

1045
01:28:52,924 --> 01:28:55,952
Who's the girl?
- It's his private secretary.

1046
01:28:56,032 --> 01:28:58,512
Miss Malti Chaudhary.
- How do you know that?

1047
01:28:59,932 --> 01:29:01,921
I had been to his office.

1048
01:29:02,699 --> 01:29:05,426
But he even refused
to acknowledge me!

1049
01:29:05,602 --> 01:29:07,841
Didn't he acknowledge you?!
- Yes, he didn't!

1050
01:29:07,921 --> 01:29:09,922
And he threw me out,
short of pushing me!

1051
01:29:10,002 --> 01:29:11,430
He dare do that!

1052
01:29:12,790 --> 01:29:14,623
It's good that he
didn't push you out.

1053
01:29:15,074 --> 01:29:17,037
Or I'd have thrown him
out of the house!

1054
01:29:17,117 --> 01:29:21,807
You live up to my expectations!
- How is our daughter-in-law?

1055
01:29:24,198 --> 01:29:26,247
How do I tell you?

1056
01:29:26,327 --> 01:29:30,338
She's miserable, thinking of
your son all the time!

1057
01:29:31,167 --> 01:29:33,407
Her hair is unruly
and uncombed...

1058
01:29:33,487 --> 01:29:35,212
her cheeks are dry!

1059
01:29:35,486 --> 01:29:37,607
Her eye-balls seem eager to
pop out of the sockets!

1060
01:29:37,687 --> 01:29:41,176
And she goes around the
village in a trance!

1061
01:29:41,256 --> 01:29:43,687
And she cries and
wants to know...

1062
01:29:44,050 --> 01:29:46,282
why her husband
has deserted her!

1063
01:29:46,816 --> 01:29:51,763
He will come, won't he?
Won't he accept me she asks!

1064
01:29:54,480 --> 01:29:59,003
Hey, stop it....
Don't cry.

1065
01:29:59,433 --> 01:30:04,747
Stop crying, Shreekant!
He will certainly accept her!

1066
01:30:06,287 --> 01:30:10,173
I will deal with the ass now!

1067
01:30:11,232 --> 01:30:17,206
If I don't impose a curfew
on his love-affair...

1068
01:30:17,426 --> 01:30:19,737
I won't claim to be
a good husband!

1069
01:30:20,100 --> 01:30:22,517
Go on now and continue
playing the private-eye.

1070
01:30:22,730 --> 01:30:28,167
Let me know, if you
smell something fishy.

1071
01:30:28,604 --> 01:30:35,559
Only you can save my sister's
life from ruination, sir!

1072
01:30:35,904 --> 01:30:40,036
Or your son is making
attempt to destroy her!

1073
01:30:40,538 --> 01:30:44,077
I must leave now.
Good-bye!

1074
01:30:51,429 --> 01:30:56,127
Why did you attend office,
when you aren't keeping well?

1075
01:30:56,418 --> 01:30:59,311
How'd I have met you, if
I didn't attend office?

1076
01:30:59,850 --> 01:31:04,010
You don't have to attend
office till I come, too.

1077
01:31:04,090 --> 01:31:07,836
How can I possibly
bunk office?

1078
01:31:07,916 --> 01:31:11,993
Very well. But do call me
from the office.

1079
01:31:13,250 --> 01:31:15,221
You will call me, won't you?
- Sure, I will.

1080
01:31:25,117 --> 01:31:26,437
What will happen now.

1081
01:31:27,149 --> 01:31:29,397
A wedding.
- What?

1082
01:31:30,018 --> 01:31:33,291
If Amit loves that girl, he'll
surely want to marry her.

1083
01:31:33,371 --> 01:31:35,078
I'll throw him out of
the house for that!

1084
01:31:35,613 --> 01:31:36,951
The ant has sprouted wings!

1085
01:31:39,498 --> 01:31:41,957
That sounds like Amit's car.
But at this hour?

1086
01:31:52,532 --> 01:31:56,719
There's a girl with Amit.
Can you see?

1087
01:31:56,799 --> 01:31:59,202
How can I? I'm not
wearing my glasses!

1088
01:31:59,282 --> 01:32:01,771
I can't see properly
without my glasses either.

1089
01:32:01,983 --> 01:32:05,033
But I'm sure it's
the same wretch!

1090
01:32:16,679 --> 01:32:18,135
What's wrong, son?

1091
01:32:18,901 --> 01:32:21,457
You're running a temperature!
Come along quickly...

1092
01:32:21,855 --> 01:32:26,109
Lie down on the bed.

1093
01:32:30,128 --> 01:32:33,682
Call the doctor.
My condition is worsening.

1094
01:32:33,762 --> 01:32:35,217
Yes, I will.

1095
01:32:36,154 --> 01:32:38,718
But who was the girl
with you, Amit?

1096
01:32:40,068 --> 01:32:42,637
It was my secretary.

1097
01:32:42,835 --> 01:32:47,098
She came to drop me home,
because I wasn't well.

1098
01:32:48,621 --> 01:32:52,119
You could have called
us over to fetch you.

1099
01:32:55,412 --> 01:32:57,186
Greetings, sir.
The keys.

1100
01:32:57,497 --> 01:32:59,747
Who was the girl, Biharilal?

1101
01:33:03,149 --> 01:33:04,684
Who was she?

1102
01:33:05,033 --> 01:33:07,359
It was Miss Malti.
The master's private.

1103
01:33:07,439 --> 01:33:11,195
Private what?
- His private secretary.

1104
01:33:11,979 --> 01:33:14,092
What were they discussing
in the car?

1105
01:33:15,343 --> 01:33:18,560
Don't feel shy. Tell us what
they were talking about.

1106
01:33:18,640 --> 01:33:20,923
I couldn't hear them well.

1107
01:33:21,003 --> 01:33:24,998
But the master called her
by the name Darjeeling.

1108
01:33:25,192 --> 01:33:28,007
Could they be going
to Darjeeling then?

1109
01:33:28,087 --> 01:33:30,131
Shut up! You're an idiot!

1110
01:33:30,814 --> 01:33:33,085
He's called her a darling!

1111
01:33:33,638 --> 01:33:36,532
Did you see anything
for yourself, Biharilal?

1112
01:33:36,612 --> 01:33:41,406
I could watch them in the
rear-view mirror, madam.

1113
01:33:41,844 --> 01:33:46,103
The young master lay in
the girl's lap!

1114
01:33:47,450 --> 01:33:52,350
The lady was muttering
sweet-nothings to him...

1115
01:33:52,878 --> 01:33:56,925
while the master's
temperature kept increasing...

1116
01:33:57,005 --> 01:34:00,960
and I kept feeling
embarrassed!

1117
01:34:01,245 --> 01:34:06,700
What happened then?
- The master then gave it to her.

1118
01:34:06,780 --> 01:34:08,397
What?
- Two time.

1119
01:34:08,477 --> 01:34:09,715
Twice kissed.

1120
01:34:09,795 --> 01:34:11,365
Gave what?
- Don't you understand?

1121
01:34:11,960 --> 01:34:15,125
Your son has kissed her!

1122
01:34:17,238 --> 01:34:19,912
She dare do that!
- How's the girl to blame?

1123
01:34:19,992 --> 01:34:21,557
It was your son
who kissed her!

1124
01:34:21,637 --> 01:34:24,763
The question is why did she
allow him to kiss her?

1125
01:34:25,516 --> 01:34:29,480
And why did this idiot
watch them kissing?!

1126
01:34:30,045 --> 01:34:34,365
Let me deal with you,
you peeping-tom...

1127
01:34:38,772 --> 01:34:42,512
Who's Malti Chaudhary
in this office?

1128
01:34:42,592 --> 01:34:43,902
Malti?

1129
01:34:45,313 --> 01:34:48,139
Who are you, sir?
- And who are you?

1130
01:34:48,775 --> 01:34:51,499
Kumar Chatterji, the chief
accountant of this company.

1131
01:34:51,579 --> 01:34:52,742
Chief accountant?
- Yes.

1132
01:34:52,822 --> 01:34:54,814
My name is
Sadanand Chaudhary.

1133
01:34:55,522 --> 01:35:01,159
The boss's father?
Greetings, sir.

1134
01:35:01,239 --> 01:35:02,942
I want to meet
Malti Chaudhary.

1135
01:35:03,097 --> 01:35:05,317
She's in her cabin.
Please follow me.

1136
01:35:11,934 --> 01:35:15,889
She seems to have
gone out on some work.

1137
01:35:15,969 --> 01:35:19,998
But do sit inside
and wait for her.

1138
01:35:23,201 --> 01:35:25,298
Please sit down.
You too, madam.

1139
01:35:26,095 --> 01:35:28,840
I want to ask you
something, Chatterji.

1140
01:35:28,920 --> 01:35:31,998
I'll explain everything
without any questions.

1141
01:35:32,078 --> 01:35:34,259
I've spread the word of
your son's love-affair...

1142
01:35:34,339 --> 01:35:36,219
in the whole city!

1143
01:35:37,717 --> 01:35:38,975
Since when has this
affair been going on?

1144
01:35:39,055 --> 01:35:40,686
Since it began, sir.

1145
01:35:40,901 --> 01:35:43,535
And when did it begin?
- Since it got going.

1146
01:35:44,341 --> 01:35:46,197
That woman, who has
enticed my son,...

1147
01:35:46,277 --> 01:35:48,499
has she been into this sort
of a thing even earlier?

1148
01:35:48,977 --> 01:35:51,991
You're mistaken, madam.

1149
01:35:52,355 --> 01:35:53,851
There's nothing wrong
with the girl.

1150
01:35:54,141 --> 01:35:56,419
In fact, she was madly
in love with me.

1151
01:35:56,895 --> 01:35:58,555
It was your son Amit...

1152
01:35:59,059 --> 01:36:02,525
who threatened me with a
transfer to Nicobar Islands...

1153
01:36:02,789 --> 01:36:04,601
and won the game by
unfair means!

1154
01:36:06,442 --> 01:36:09,031
It is I who will send the
girl to the back-waters!

1155
01:36:09,773 --> 01:36:13,222
You will be happy to know,
Mr Chatterjee, that...

1156
01:36:13,610 --> 01:36:17,068
I'm not against occasionally
beating up silly women!

1157
01:36:17,332 --> 01:36:18,660
Am I not right?
- Nonsense!

1158
01:36:18,950 --> 01:36:21,061
It's always the men
who are at fault!

1159
01:36:21,360 --> 01:36:24,615
It's they who deserve a thrashing!
- You're right, madam!

1160
01:36:24,695 --> 01:36:27,105
It's the boss who ought
to be beaten up!

1161
01:36:27,422 --> 01:36:30,185
As for Malti Chaudhary...
I'll handle her myself!

1162
01:36:30,677 --> 01:36:31,812
Well, all right.

1163
01:36:32,327 --> 01:36:35,984
Do warn Malti Chaudhary then,
that if she doesn't relent...

1164
01:36:36,366 --> 01:36:37,761
I'll make life difficult
for her!

1165
01:36:52,097 --> 01:36:54,367
What are you weighing
in the scale?

1166
01:36:54,607 --> 01:36:56,681
The pros and cons,
naturally!

1167
01:36:57,549 --> 01:36:58,984
Won't you listen to me?

1168
01:37:01,810 --> 01:37:04,412
My in-laws visited the
office today.

1169
01:37:04,936 --> 01:37:06,224
And from what I've heard...

1170
01:37:06,792 --> 01:37:09,483
they're longing for their
daughter-in-law.

1171
01:37:12,138 --> 01:37:14,061
I don't like this anymore!

1172
01:37:14,645 --> 01:37:16,900
Tell me, Shreekant...

1173
01:37:17,673 --> 01:37:20,806
why must we punish them,
when they are innocent?

1174
01:37:21,184 --> 01:37:23,919
You are right!

1175
01:37:24,209 --> 01:37:25,924
What do you mean?
- All I mean is that...

1176
01:37:26,004 --> 01:37:29,178
had you not been secretary
to him, someone else would.

1177
01:37:29,416 --> 01:37:30,719
And whoever she
might have been,...

1178
01:37:30,799 --> 01:37:32,805
she'd have weighed
heavier on his mind!

1179
01:37:33,138 --> 01:37:35,512
Somewhat like this!

1180
01:37:37,291 --> 01:37:41,754
You have the upper hand today
because he's smitten by you.

1181
01:37:43,687 --> 01:37:47,128
Or else, he'd have fallen
for another woman by now.

1182
01:37:49,969 --> 01:37:51,921
Let's continue with the game.

1183
01:37:52,529 --> 01:37:55,622
There are many days and
nights yet to come.

1184
01:37:56,302 --> 01:37:57,886
There's a lot to speak about.

1185
01:38:11,374 --> 01:38:13,614
Is the driver here, Ramu?
- Yes, sir.

1186
01:38:13,921 --> 01:38:15,290
But the Master's
taking the car away.

1187
01:38:15,370 --> 01:38:16,629
Where to?
- Nirmal Village.

1188
01:38:16,709 --> 01:38:17,394
Chandanpur?
- Yes.

1189
01:38:17,474 --> 01:38:20,482
Yes. I suggest you take
leave, and accompany us.

1190
01:38:20,562 --> 01:38:22,307
What for?
- To bring your wife home.

1191
01:38:22,542 --> 01:38:24,240
What's made you decide
this, all of a sudden?

1192
01:38:24,320 --> 01:38:26,342
It wasn't sudden.
We made the decision...

1193
01:38:26,422 --> 01:38:28,321
only after hearing a lot and
seeing it for ourselves, too!

1194
01:38:28,401 --> 01:38:30,604
Sure. Go ahead.

1195
01:38:30,684 --> 01:38:33,560
I must attend the office
to check the accounts.

1196
01:38:33,640 --> 01:38:36,109
I've already checked that out
at your office yesterday!

1197
01:38:36,374 --> 01:38:38,884
They don't speak highly of
you; in fact, you're infamous!

1198
01:38:39,100 --> 01:38:41,501
You'd better correct that or
the company stands to lose a lot!

1199
01:38:41,833 --> 01:38:45,748
We'll go ahead, if you
don't want to come along.

1200
01:38:45,828 --> 01:38:46,828
Let's go.

1201
01:38:50,157 --> 01:38:52,453
Daughter-in-law, my foot!

1202
01:39:07,834 --> 01:39:11,691
What are you dressed in?
- I want to marry you!

1203
01:39:11,961 --> 01:39:14,014
What?!
- Yes! Right now!

1204
01:39:15,068 --> 01:39:19,001
Right now? But I'd have to
seek my parents' consent.

1205
01:39:19,367 --> 01:39:22,525
Introduce me to them.
Everything's going haywire!

1206
01:39:22,605 --> 01:39:25,820
Haywire?!
- Yes! I can't wait anymore!

1207
01:39:26,331 --> 01:39:28,255
Won't you seek the blessings
of your own parents, then?

1208
01:39:28,547 --> 01:39:31,080
I'll manage with your
parents' blessings!

1209
01:39:31,160 --> 01:39:32,690
So when are you introducing
me to them?

1210
01:39:33,270 --> 01:39:36,728
I'd have to find them, I guess...
- Find them?!

1211
01:39:36,808 --> 01:39:40,026
They must've gone shopping.
But I'll find them.

1212
01:39:40,106 --> 01:39:44,008
I'll come at 6 this evening
to meet them then, okay?

1213
01:39:53,820 --> 01:39:56,537
Have you spent the night
at the office, sir?

1214
01:39:57,058 --> 01:40:00,005
Why are you in your
night-dress, sir?

1215
01:40:03,912 --> 01:40:08,032
Your in-laws have gone to the village
to bring you home?

1216
01:40:08,747 --> 01:40:10,766
And your husband is
coming here...

1217
01:40:10,846 --> 01:40:12,818
to meet your so-called
parents, right?

1218
01:40:13,111 --> 01:40:14,747
What will we do now?

1219
01:40:15,243 --> 01:40:19,410
lf both secrets are out,
all hell will break loose!

1220
01:40:22,721 --> 01:40:24,202
Don't worry!

1221
01:40:24,282 --> 01:40:27,743
I suggest you handle
your husband.

1222
01:40:27,823 --> 01:40:31,756
You're a great actress anyway!

1223
01:40:32,399 --> 01:40:36,199
And I'll handle the
problem in the village.

1224
01:40:36,279 --> 01:40:38,926
What do you think of that?
- That's okay.

1225
01:40:39,006 --> 01:40:40,941
But where will I find
a fake-Mom from?

1226
01:40:41,021 --> 01:40:44,390
There's a solution
to every problem!

1227
01:40:44,470 --> 01:40:47,522
When everything in the city
is available on hire...

1228
01:40:47,602 --> 01:40:49,862
won't we find a pair
of parents?

1229
01:40:59,430 --> 01:41:00,512
Please come...

1230
01:41:03,991 --> 01:41:05,319
Greetings.
- Greetings.

1231
01:41:05,399 --> 01:41:08,566
Kantibhai! He has arrived!

1232
01:41:15,862 --> 01:41:16,997
Greetings...

1233
01:41:20,144 --> 01:41:21,807
How are you?

1234
01:41:23,619 --> 01:41:31,273
Where has she gone....?
She's a strange woman!

1235
01:41:31,898 --> 01:41:34,915
Kantibhai...!

1236
01:41:34,995 --> 01:41:37,607
Where the hell are you?

1237
01:41:43,711 --> 01:41:46,782
Where are you?

1238
01:42:01,900 --> 01:42:04,502
They appear to be brother and sister.
And where are your parents?

1239
01:42:04,582 --> 01:42:08,519
They're are my parents!
My mother is a Gujarati...

1240
01:42:08,599 --> 01:42:11,180
which is why she addresses
him as bhai (brother).

1241
01:42:11,918 --> 01:42:13,994
Are you a Guajarati then?
- Yes.

1242
01:42:14,074 --> 01:42:16,642
My Mom is Guajarati;
my father is a Bengali.

1243
01:42:23,822 --> 01:42:25,071
Greetings!
-Greetings!

1244
01:42:25,151 --> 01:42:28,402
Do sit down...
-Please sit.

1245
01:42:29,348 --> 01:42:30,755
Sit on this chair.

1246
01:42:42,298 --> 01:42:43,670
Evening is all right!

1247
01:42:45,219 --> 01:42:48,694
You're just as my daughter
described you!

1248
01:42:48,774 --> 01:42:51,122
Tall and fair-skinned;
those blue eyes...

1249
01:42:51,202 --> 01:42:54,156
they remind me of
film-star Raj Kapoor!

1250
01:42:55,757 --> 01:42:58,337
Our daughter is no less!

1251
01:42:58,739 --> 01:43:01,428
She's fair-skinned
and beautiful...

1252
01:43:01,508 --> 01:43:03,490
a real princess!

1253
01:43:07,179 --> 01:43:10,457
D'you know what is
special about you?

1254
01:43:10,910 --> 01:43:16,609
It's your moustache!
it's real, isn't it?

1255
01:43:16,689 --> 01:43:18,989
Of course! As real
as yours !

1256
01:43:21,211 --> 01:43:23,167
Mine are real, too!

1257
01:43:23,247 --> 01:43:25,638
That's because my wife
loves a moustache!

1258
01:43:25,807 --> 01:43:29,097
Undoubtedly! A moustache
spells masculinity.

1259
01:43:29,643 --> 01:43:33,962
I married Kantibhai only
because he had a moustache.

1260
01:43:34,154 --> 01:43:37,269
And since you have a moustache, too
my daughter has approved of you!

1261
01:43:37,582 --> 01:43:39,469
We will certainly give you
our daughter in marriage!

1262
01:43:39,814 --> 01:43:41,678
But you will be a responsible
man, won't you?

1263
01:43:41,758 --> 01:43:43,974
Of course! I will!

1264
01:43:44,789 --> 01:43:46,590
How much of a bank-balance
do you have?

1265
01:43:47,161 --> 01:43:48,570
My bank-balance? What for?

1266
01:43:49,048 --> 01:43:52,158
It has to do with responsibilities.
Only a moustache won't do!

1267
01:43:54,600 --> 01:43:56,417
I must have about
3 or 3.5 lakh Rupees.

1268
01:43:56,497 --> 01:43:58,922
Not 4.5 lakh Rupees?
- Sure. Must be.

1269
01:44:02,815 --> 01:44:06,425
He has about 4.5 lakh Rupees.
We can easily ask for 80000 Rupees!

1270
01:44:06,505 --> 01:44:09,640
No! We need a lakh!
- Let's settle for 80000!

1271
01:44:09,720 --> 01:44:13,013
Well okay. One lakh, it will be.
- A lakh? What could that mean?

1272
01:44:13,204 --> 01:44:17,540
A lakh must be paid, since you're
marrying our daughter.

1273
01:44:17,620 --> 01:44:19,810
No thank you! I will
not accept a penny!

1274
01:44:20,224 --> 01:44:23,930
Not accept! You will have
to pay us a lakh instead!

1275
01:44:28,983 --> 01:44:30,052
Pay you?!

1276
01:44:30,132 --> 01:44:33,311
As dowry. How can there be
a marriage without dowry?

1277
01:44:33,391 --> 01:44:35,352
This is a totally
wrong system!

1278
01:44:35,432 --> 01:44:37,342
On the contrary, you
ought to be happy...

1279
01:44:37,422 --> 01:44:40,280
that I'm willing to marry your
daughter without any dowry.

1280
01:44:40,360 --> 01:44:42,432
And here you are... asking me
to pay the dowry!

1281
01:44:44,262 --> 01:44:46,571
What are you talking
about, Mom?!

1282
01:44:46,651 --> 01:44:49,125
We're marrying since
we love each other!

1283
01:44:50,991 --> 01:44:55,642
Haven't we toiled to
bring you up, my dear?

1284
01:44:56,489 --> 01:44:59,172
Do you wish to light up your
house after your marriage...

1285
01:44:59,446 --> 01:45:01,402
and plunge our home
in darkness?

1286
01:45:01,873 --> 01:45:03,548
A lakh of Rupees!
- A lakh?

1287
01:45:03,942 --> 01:45:06,360
Or 50 thousand cash and 200
gram gold.

1288
01:45:06,754 --> 01:45:08,823
If have then give it or get go.

1289
01:45:08,903 --> 01:45:13,616
Radhe Shyam Jhunghun's son has ready
to give 2 lakh rupees for our daughter.

1290
01:45:13,696 --> 01:45:15,313
Am I right, darling?
- Yes.

1291
01:45:17,641 --> 01:45:21,090
It's a very reasonable deal!
Grab it!

1292
01:45:21,512 --> 01:45:25,081
That's not much for love, is it?
- Do you believe that, too?

1293
01:45:25,651 --> 01:45:29,606
Actually, to accept dowry is
considered a social crime.

1294
01:45:29,874 --> 01:45:32,583
Besides, we love each other.

1295
01:45:33,702 --> 01:45:35,716
We'll give you a 10/o
discount, in that case.

1296
01:45:37,405 --> 01:45:40,882
I know it's a crime to
ask for dowry, son.

1297
01:45:40,962 --> 01:45:44,845
I know that very well
because I'm a woman!

1298
01:45:45,141 --> 01:45:49,104
I know how the cancer of
dowry is destroying us!

1299
01:45:49,553 --> 01:45:52,292
Our parents are coerced
into paying dowry!

1300
01:45:52,372 --> 01:45:55,304
And thereafter begins
a sage of atrocities!

1301
01:45:55,600 --> 01:45:59,647
What is that for? Because men
consider women to be worth nothing!

1302
01:45:59,727 --> 01:46:04,419
You think women are weak
and helpless parasites!

1303
01:46:04,499 --> 01:46:08,352
But it's not true!
We will prove otherwise!

1304
01:46:10,415 --> 01:46:15,384
We will prove that women are
not weak and helpless!

1305
01:46:15,464 --> 01:46:18,358
Long live, Women's Lib!

1306
01:46:25,262 --> 01:46:26,188
Well, all right!

1307
01:46:26,268 --> 01:46:29,984
Please give me some time
to think it over.

1308
01:46:33,938 --> 01:46:36,442
Listen to me, darling.

1309
01:46:36,522 --> 01:46:38,961
Don't take offence at what
my parents said!

1310
01:46:39,041 --> 01:46:44,082
Don't take offence?! Your father's
a butcher, as far as money goes!

1311
01:46:45,490 --> 01:46:48,744
How can I help it?
That's how all parents are!

1312
01:46:48,824 --> 01:46:52,343
Why I can't figure this out is
because ours is a different case!

1313
01:46:52,423 --> 01:46:56,512
There's no money
in a love-marriage!

1314
01:46:56,829 --> 01:47:00,184
You don't know my old man!
He wouldn't part with a penny!

1315
01:47:00,264 --> 01:47:01,959
But if you want to
marry me...

1316
01:47:02,039 --> 01:47:04,125
you'll have to agree to the
conditions of my parents.

1317
01:47:04,205 --> 01:47:06,882
I suggest you find
a part-time job.

1318
01:47:06,962 --> 01:47:09,101
I? A part-time job?

1319
01:47:09,533 --> 01:47:12,744
They're the only parents I have!

1320
01:47:12,824 --> 01:47:14,651
Besides, what don't people do in love?

1321
01:47:15,190 --> 01:47:17,138
Can't you do even
this much for me?

1322
01:47:18,103 --> 01:47:20,705
Sure, I will. I will have to!

1323
01:47:46,348 --> 01:47:48,560
Where could they have gone?
- How would I know!

1324
01:47:48,640 --> 01:47:50,738
Mr Chaudhary?! Greetings!

1325
01:47:51,234 --> 01:47:53,425
What brings you here?

1326
01:47:54,795 --> 01:47:56,956
Where have they gone,
Teacher?

1327
01:47:57,280 --> 01:47:59,070
How do I narrate their
tale of woes.

1328
01:47:59,150 --> 01:48:02,289
Ever since that
shameful day...

1329
01:48:03,028 --> 01:48:05,395
Madhuri and her mother
left the village for good.

1330
01:48:05,475 --> 01:48:07,028
For good?!

1331
01:48:07,108 --> 01:48:09,125
After the humiliation they
were subjected to...

1332
01:48:09,205 --> 01:48:11,122
they chose to leave
the village.

1333
01:48:11,202 --> 01:48:13,215
They should have died
of shame, actually!

1334
01:48:13,295 --> 01:48:17,008
No! Please don't say that!
Shreekant called on us in the city.

1335
01:48:17,088 --> 01:48:18,916
But he didn't tell us
a word of this.

1336
01:48:20,913 --> 01:48:25,259
See the lock your jokes
have put on the door!

1337
01:48:25,593 --> 01:48:28,645
Do you have the keys
to unlock it then?

1338
01:48:28,988 --> 01:48:31,276
It will never open again!

1339
01:48:31,672 --> 01:48:33,053
You can open locks
made of iron...

1340
01:48:33,133 --> 01:48:36,613
but never one that opens
the doors to the hearts!

1341
01:49:03,493 --> 01:49:04,619
Come on out.

1342
01:49:08,912 --> 01:49:12,212
What farce is
Shreekant playing?

1343
01:49:12,292 --> 01:49:14,350
My daughter's in-laws have
returned from our door!

1344
01:49:14,430 --> 01:49:19,136
They had once returned because
their son asked them to.

1345
01:49:19,717 --> 01:49:22,280
And they return today,
since your son wants them to.

1346
01:49:22,620 --> 01:49:23,930
Let's go inside.

1347
01:49:27,168 --> 01:49:28,294
Thanks a lot, Teacher.

1348
01:49:32,991 --> 01:49:36,985
I was looking for you!
Here's a bouquet!

1349
01:49:37,363 --> 01:49:38,762
What's up?

1350
01:49:38,973 --> 01:49:42,598
How have got to the bouquet
from a single rose?

1351
01:49:42,678 --> 01:49:46,858
For what the boss has done,
you deserve a bouquet!

1352
01:49:46,938 --> 01:49:49,917
And I also want to
congratulate you!

1353
01:49:49,997 --> 01:49:52,160
What for?
- I'll explain.

1354
01:49:54,747 --> 01:49:58,512
Amit has lost! I've won the day! 
And you're a free bird!

1355
01:49:58,776 --> 01:50:00,891
I wasn't a captive earlier, was I?

1356
01:50:00,971 --> 01:50:04,122
It is something of the sort.
I'll explain. Sit down.

1357
01:50:06,255 --> 01:50:10,371
Amit wanted to imprison
you in a marriage...

1358
01:50:10,451 --> 01:50:13,371
and wanted to have
all the fun by himself!

1359
01:50:13,451 --> 01:50:16,331
But his plans have flopped!
D'you know why?

1360
01:50:17,050 --> 01:50:19,716
Because he's already
a married man!

1361
01:50:20,217 --> 01:50:23,033
His brother-in-law came here
to meet him the other day.

1362
01:50:23,113 --> 01:50:25,771
And without even divorcing
the village belle...

1363
01:50:25,851 --> 01:50:28,173
the rascal's trying to
lure you into wedlock!

1364
01:50:29,128 --> 01:50:32,145
We are both free now!

1365
01:50:32,225 --> 01:50:36,930
The love-story that had
just begun will now blossom!

1366
01:50:37,010 --> 01:50:41,293
But remember! I will not
spare the hypocrite!

1367
01:50:42,059 --> 01:50:44,866
I am throwing a party
tomorrow to expose him!

1368
01:50:44,946 --> 01:50:47,716
And on the occasion of his
fourth wedding anniversary...

1369
01:50:47,796 --> 01:50:50,416
you will see how the
guests ridicule him!

1370
01:50:52,607 --> 01:50:54,288
What are you getting
angry at me for?

1371
01:50:54,368 --> 01:50:58,537
You should be angry
with the fraud, who...

1372
01:51:00,974 --> 01:51:03,462
I'm coming over.

1373
01:51:08,830 --> 01:51:11,180
Let's continue playing
the game, sister.

1374
01:51:11,260 --> 01:51:13,925
There's a lot more
yet to come.

1375
01:51:14,373 --> 01:51:16,230
A lot more to discuss.

1376
01:51:20,946 --> 01:51:22,788
"What was he in reality..."

1377
01:51:22,868 --> 01:51:27,491
"and what did I take him for"

1378
01:51:34,581 --> 01:51:41,158
"How could I revere
a stone-hearted man?"

1379
01:51:41,238 --> 01:51:43,314
"What was he in reality"

1380
01:51:43,394 --> 01:51:47,618
"And what did take him for"

1381
01:52:08,544 --> 01:52:15,074
"All he wanted to do was
to play with my feelings"

1382
01:52:18,512 --> 01:52:24,442
"All he wanted to do was
to play with my feelings"

1383
01:52:24,750 --> 01:52:31,277
"And I thought I was
betrothed to him for life"

1384
01:52:31,357 --> 01:52:32,932
"What was he in reality"

1385
01:52:33,012 --> 01:52:37,616
"And what did I take him for"

1386
01:53:01,729 --> 01:53:07,656
"The face was supposed to
